title: spud stick party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
butter.
Melt
butter
and pour over mix.
Spread on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.	Cool.

title: seashell tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper sauce.
Stir in macaroni, tuna, celery, onion and green pepper.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Toss before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fudgy oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, 1 cup butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in oats.
Reserve 1/3 of the oat mixture.
Press remaining oat mixture in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: cherry-walnut bars
directions: Combine soft butter and powdered sugar with enough cherry liquid to spread.
Frost.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with beef and wrap each breast with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Lightly pepper.
Combine soup, sour cream and cheese and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, salt and pepper. Stir in corn, onion, pimento; mix well.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Toss butter with the rest of cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half; cook in boiling water until tender and drain. While spaghetti is warm, combine with eggs and parmesan cheese, and pour into well greased 10 inch pie pan. Gently press mixture up and around sides. Saute onions in melted butter, cool and stir in sour cream, gently place over spaghetti mixture. combine sausage, tomato paste and water, pour over sour cream mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and allow to melt. Serve hot.

title: pudding fluff
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together. Mix in pudding. Stir in pie filling. Stir until all ingredients are blended. Serve alone or with pound cake.

title: chicken divine
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer broccoli and chicken in bottom.
Combine mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 5 servings.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until very light; add milk.
Sift and fold in the flour and sugar.
Add cream, butter and milk.
Bake in large cakes on a hot griddle.
Place 2 tablespoons fresh sweetened strawberries on each cake and roll up.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or top with Cool Whip.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into chunks and coat with flour and salt.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in large container and bake in medium hot oven for 48 hours.
Serves 3800 people.
If you are expecting a larger crowd, put in the rabbit.
Don't do this unless it's necessary, as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix first 6 items together well.
Form into balls.
Bake in shallow pan 1 hour at 300°.
Drain off grease, then cover with last 6 items cooked until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over balls.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
This can be frozen before baking last 15 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: scotch shortbreads
directions: In electric mixer, beat butter; add sugar gradually and flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Fold in last half cup of flour by hand.
Roll in 1/3-inch thick, cut in squares or rounds, price with fork and decorate, if desired.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in moderate 350° oven or until delicately brown.
Makes 24 or more.

title: chocolate chip macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and Macadamia nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Cut all vegetables julienne style and add to pan.
Stir-fry until tender.
Add salt to taste and heavy cream.
Heat to just boiling.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: layered salad
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the lettuce, eggs, bacon, onion and peas.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing mix and seal the salad with it.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add enough milk to make mixture the consistency of corn bread. Cook at 450° in iron skillet until just lightly brown. Break up. Add chicken (or turkey) broth, onion and celery (chopped fine) and eggs. (Make soupy.) Cook 1 hour at 400°.

title: sunday morning breakfast
directions: Butter pan.
Put bread slices in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread butter on top of bread.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese on top of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and salt together.
Pour on top of bread and sausage/cheese layers.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in chicken broth, about 30 minutes or until tender. Add butter. Cool slightly and pure.
Stir in seasonings, milk and parsley.
Serve hot.
Freezes well.

title: slovenian italian pasta sauce
directions: Heat a 5-quart saucepan.
Add olive oil to hot pan.
Add Italian sausage cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces and cook until brown, then push sausage to one side of pan.
Add chicken liver that has been chopped very fine or chopped in a food processor.
(Chop when still half frozen.)
Cook a few minutes and mix with sausage.
Push to one side and saute chopped onions and cook until transparent, then mix ingredients together.
Then add your sauce, paste, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Add just enough water to make thick sauce.
When sauce begins to boil, add cheese and mushrooms. Simmer 2 to 3 hours, the longer the better the sauce.
Stir often. Good for any kind of pasta.

title: chicken a la james beard(with 40 cloves of garlic provencale recipe)
directions: *Cooked garlic will have no after taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: hot fruit dip
directions: Mix together and heat in microwave until creamy.
Serve with fruit.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve in boiling water, the Jell-O.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Stir in applesauce.
Makes 10 servings.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Place cooked rice in bottom of casserole dish then cooked broccoli over rice.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz in onions and celery until all is smooth.
Pour over broccoli and rice.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
You can freeze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Double recipe for 2 pies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix everything together. Pour into a chocolate crumb crust. Refrigerate.

title: fruit sparkle topping
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in water.
Add fruit cocktail liquid and orange juice concentrate.
Cook and stir until thick and boiling.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts.
Chill.
Serve as a sundae sauce or over pound cake.
Makes topping for 24 sundaes or about 5 cups.

title: fried deer
directions: Cut up 1 large, fat hen (6 to 8 pounds) and put in a large pot to cook until tender.
Make sure to have enough broth on the chicken.
Put aside about a quart of broth for the dumplings. Take the broth and add to the flour. Keep adding flour to broth until the dough is very stiff.
If you use plain flour, add salt. If you use self-rising flour, do not add salt.
Divide the dough into 2 parts.
Roll until thin.
Cut and drop dumplings into boiling broth.
Let cook until done.
Never stir dumplings.
Shake pot to keep dumplings from sticking.
This is an old recipe, handed down in the family.

title: snicker - bar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs and rest of ingredients. Shape into 2 rolls and chill.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy horseradish herb dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix milk and cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients. Blend well until creamy. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix the first five ingredients.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased cake pan or glass dish.
Cover with diced rhubarb. Combine granulated sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb mixture and cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate rolled oats cookies
directions: Rinse and drain raisins.
Cream shortening; add sugar and then well-beaten eggs.
Add melted chocolate and mix thoroughly.
Then add sifted dry ingredients, oats, raisins and flavoring.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets and bake in a moderate 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool on rack or clean newspaper. Makes 2 and 1/2 dozen cookies.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: scrumptious brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
(Or heat chocolate and butter at High power in nonmetal bowl in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Then stir until melted and smooth.)
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl on high speed for 10 minutes.
Blend chocolate mixture on low speed.
Add flour, beating just to blend.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool in pan, then cut into squares.
Makes 32 brownies.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in julienne strips.
Steam until just tender.
Mix sugar, butter and cinnamon in large skillet.
Cook and stir until well blended.
Add carrots.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until carrots are shiny and well glazed (about 5 minutes).
Makes 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Cube bacon and fry until crisp.
Pour off fat.
Add hamburg and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Do not stir too much. Place in casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for one hour.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, relish, salad dressing, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Add ground meat and mix well.
Pat meat mixture into 8 x 12-inch rectangle on wax paper.
Top with sauerkraut and cheese.
Beginning at short end, roll by lifting end of wax paper.
Press ends to seal.
Place seam side down on a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle top with cheese.
Turn off oven.
Return to oven to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grate zucchini (coarse) unpeeled.
Add cracker crumbs, bacon and egg.
Saute mushrooms, butter, onion and garlic.
Add to other mixture and put into buttered casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: red party punch
directions: Mix all liquids together in punch bowl; let chill 2 hours. When ready to serve, cut ice cream into four squares; let float on top of punch.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Generously grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine the flours, sugars, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add oil, vanilla and the eggs; beat until well mixed.
Stir in chopped apples and walnuts.
Spoon batter evenly into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then on rack.
Cool thoroughly.
Drizzle top with Powdered Sugar Glaze or whipped cream.
Makes 16 servings.

title: wet burrito casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add mushrooms, seasoning and beans just to heat.
Put hamburger mixture in taco shells.
Place in pan on top of sour cream mixture.
Top with remaining sour cream mixture, then cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pudding mix
directions: For vanilla pudding, add 1 tablespoon vanilla flavoring.

title: old fashion baked rice pudding(high calcium recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a lightly buttered 2 quart casserole, combine milk, rice, sugar and salt.
Bake, uncovered for 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes, adding raisins during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Stir in surface crust.
As rice stands, it will absorb milk remaining in casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve warm or chilled.
Add additional milk if desired.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain beef if desired.
In large microwavable dish, cube cheese and add chili and salsa (and beef if used).
Heat until melted, stirring often.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain and mix with all other ingredients, except crackers and margarine. Crumble crackers.
Melt butter and mix with crackers. Pour vegetables into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers on top and bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cabbage wedges
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water 12 minutes or until tender; drain. Place wedges in 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, cook green peppers and onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, salt, chocolate and syrup.
Cook over low flame until candy forms soft ball in cold water.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Beat until thick.
Pour on buttered platter until it sets.

title: cherry or blueberry yum yums
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Mix in Dream Whip. Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Pat crumbs in bottom of dish. Add pie filling and top with cream cheese mixture. Chill 1 hour.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Brown the beef.
Place in a 2-quart casserole; top with vegetables.
Combine soup and water; pour over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dill dough buns
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Blend in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and dill.
Stir until a soft dough is formed.
Knead gently on a floured board for 30 seconds.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 12 biscuits.
Bake on cookie sheet in a hot 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: meatless mexican salad
directions: Mix beans, cheese, onion, pepper, celery and dressing together. Just before serving, mix Fritos.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla and dry ingredients and blend well.
Shape into walnut size balls. Roll in sugar and flatten with fork on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 350°. Bake for 12 minutes.

title: applesauce squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Beat in flour mixture.
Add applesauce, nuts and raisins.
Mix.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: seven step salad
directions: Line glass dish with lettuce, grated carrots, onions, green peppers, cooked garden peas and celery.
Spread mayonnaise over top of salad.
Sprinkle bacon bits and Cheddar cheese over top.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan.
Add soup and water, mixed. Add a few drops of Kitchen Bouquet to the gravy mix.
Bake at 350° until pork chops are tender.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add the shortening, sugar, salt and mashed potatoes to hot potato water.
When cold, add yeast and eggs, beaten with a fork.
Sift in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on slightly floured board; knead well. Put into greased bowl; grease lightly the top of the dough and cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
When needed, form in desired shape.
Place in greased pan or muffin tin; put in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Brush with melted shortening; bake in a 375° to 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
This dough will keep in the refrigerator a week or more. Yields 30 rolls.

title: balls-o-fish
directions: Place fish in a medium sized bowl.
Combine onion, egg, crackers, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients together well.
Cut cheese into 1/2 inch squares.
Take some of the fish mixture and place one of the cheese squares inside, making sure all of the cheese is covered.
Gently place the fish ball in a deep fryer.
Cook approximately 3 to 5 minutes or until the fish floats.
Serve with sour cream.

title: shoo-fly pie(wet bottom)
directions: Dissolve baking soda in warm water.
Stir little better than 1/2 of crumb mixture into liquid mixture.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 375°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and press in loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Add green pepper rings on top. Cook in a 350° oven until done.

title: sherried orange chicken
directions: Remove excess fat from chicken breasts.
Place chicken breasts in glass or plastic bowl or heavy plastic bag.
Drain mandarin oranges and reserve the juice.
Mix sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar, oregano, garlic, and 1/3 cup of the reserved mandarin orange juice; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, turning once.
Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet until hot. Cook chicken in oil over medium heat until lightly browned on both sides; add sherry mixture.
Reduce heat; cover and cook until chicken is done, about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken; keep warm. Mix cornstarch and remaining juice; stir into hot liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute. Stir in orange segments and raisins; heat through.
Serve chicken and sauce over rice; sprinkle with chives.
230 calories per serving.

title: melinda's bars
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar over medium heat until clear.
Do NOT boil.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Add 6 cups of corn flakes and press into ungreased 13 x 9 pan.
Add 1 12 ounce package of chocolate chips to the top and place in a warm oven for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix together 1 cup crushed crackers, 1/2 cup slivered almonds and 1/2 stick melted margarine and spread on top.
Bake for 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place raw beef in roaster.
Top with onion and celery.
Mix other ingredients and pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 1/2 hours.
Shred with fork.

title: super beef and squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in salted water about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Cook green peppers and meat until meat is no longer pink. Drain.
Stir in rice.

title: chicken simplicity
directions: In bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, place rice.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Dilute soup with one can of water; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 servings.

title: tommy's famous chili recipe
directions: Cut up bell peppers and onions real fine.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in frying pan and add peppers and onions, stirring constantly so they will not burn.
Add 1/2 package of chili season mix and 1/2 package of taco mix, 1/2 cup of water, then cover and cook on low heat.

title: instant reuben casserole
directions: Lightly grease an 8 or 9-inch square baking dish. Spread mustard evenly on one side of each bread slice. Cut bread into 1/2-inch squares. (You should have about 3 1/2 cups.) Scatter bread over bottom of prepared dish. Crumble corned beef over bread.

title: chillies and cheese
directions: Mix the eggs and the water and pour over the chillies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Doritos.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice off the top of each tomato; scoop out center.
Mash Camembert, mix with other ingredients and fill tomatoes.

title: play doh
directions: Mix oil, water and desired food coloring.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring. Cool.
Put in airtight container.
Can make this with children's help.
As good or better than store bought.

title: california cheese casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions and drain. Crisp-fry bacon.
Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Blend in cheese soup, sour cream, cooked beans and crumbled bacon.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top beans with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tea cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar thoroughly. Add warm melted butter.
Add flour, one cup at a time, stirring well after each cup.

Add baking powder, blending well. Add milk and flavoring, mixing well. Flour hands and dough so dough can be handled easily. Take a tablespoon at a time and press out thin on buttered pan or cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Bake wings at 400° on flat sheet for 3 minutes.
Baste with sauce and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn and baste with remaining sauce 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serve plain or with Bleu cheese.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; add a layer of graham cracker crumbs (1 1/4 cups).
Add coconut on top.
Spread chocolate chips on top.
Spread butterscotch or peanut butter chips on top. Spread chopped nuts on top of chips, then add Eagle Brand milk over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed.
Brown beef in skillet.
Separate browned beef in half.
Add to beef in skillet tomato paste, sauce, whole tomatoes (quartered), garlic, parsley, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and oregano.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and remaining beef in separate bowl.
Pour 1/2 of sauce mixture in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stuff manicotti noodles with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over stuffed noodles.
Add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red skin potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, quartered and cleaned.
Mix next 8 ingredients and pour over cooled potatoes.
Sprinkle with fried bacon bits and green onion.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients together & chill for at least two hours before serving.

title: tessie's nut bread
directions: Beat egg in milk.
Mix dry ingredients, nut pieces and candied orange peel.
Stir in milk. Pour into greased bread pan.
With spatula spread dough to ends of pan creating an indentation in middle of dough.
Let set 20 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until a golden brown.
Remove from oven, cool for 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: pecan cheese crackers
directions: Cream butter and cheese together until well mixed.
Add chopped pecans.
Shape into rolls and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add shrimp last.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add the milk and melted oleo (butter). Pour in ungreased pan.
On top of batter, pour 1 pint or more of fruit and juice.
Add 1 cup sugar, if fruit is unsweetened.
On top of this pour 1 cup of boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: steak and potato kabobs
directions: You will need 12 wooden skewers.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine onions, consomme, butter and Worcestershire sauce in a saucepan and cook until tender.
Put a chunk of bread in each of 4 ovenproof bowls.
Pour soup over bread and top with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese has started to brown.
Serve hot.

title: pork chops, etc.
directions: Trim as much fat as possible from the pork chops. Brush with olive oil.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend together milk, juice and yolks. Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until they hold a soft peak. Gradually beat in sugar. Beat until whites hold a firm peak. Cover pie with meringue. Bake at 325° or until top is brown. Cook.

title: nannie's custard
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolk and whites in separate bowls.
Add sugar, flour and salt to yolks.
Add milk.
Fold in whites.
Add vanilla.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick. Cool.
Add desired fruit and freeze in 4-quart ice cream freezer.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake vigorously. Shake again before serving.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine oats, 1/4 cup tomato sauce, 1/4 cup sliced olives, 1 teaspoon onion and Italian seasoning.
Add ground beef; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Shape to form four 4 x 2-inch loaves or one large loaf.
Place in 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until meat is done; drain grease.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, olives, onion and garlic powder; cook over low heat 3 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Spoon over loaf; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat 1 cup of milk and use the 1/2 cup of milk to dissolve the sugar, cocoa, salt and flour that has been well blended with the beaten egg yolks.
Pour mixture into the hot milk and cook until proper consistency for pie.
Flavor, if desired.
Add butter and pour into baked crust.
Top with the beaten egg whites and brown in oven.

title: peanut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Bake crust in oven for 10 minutes, remove and set aside.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour cherries in 8 x 8 baking dish. Pour dry cake mix evenly over cherries.
Melt butter; drizzle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes until golden.

title: microwave pineapple cheese salad
directions: Pour water into a large glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in lime gelatin, marshmallows and cream cheese.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Beat until smooth. Cool.
Add pineapple and chill until thickened, but not set. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a ring mold.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Add maraschino cherries for color at Christmas.

title: microwave italian meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook at medium-high for 7 1/2 to 8 1/2 minutes.
Drain.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and crushed pineapple for 20 minutes. Take off stove and sprinkle the box of Jell-O over it and stir until dissolved.
Put in jelly jars and wax.
Very good.

title: fluffy dill biscuits(6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine first 4 ingredients and 1 tablespoon onion flakes to form a ball.
Knead on floured surface. Roll out to 1-inch thick.
Using a 3-inch heart-shaped cookie cutter, cut 6 biscuits, re-rolling scraps.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with remaining onion flakes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat cocoa, butter and Coca-Cola. Bring to a boil.
In another bowl, mix buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and stir.
Pour Coca-Cola mixture over flour, sugar mixture and mix well.
Pour milk and egg mixture in with other. Add marshmallows and stir.
Pour in greased and floured Pyrex dish (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done. (Test with a toothpick.)

title: aunt ruth's pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix well and bake in 2 frozen pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions except omit the salt.
Drain well.
Arrange broccoli spears in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Meanwhile, for sauce, in a medium saucepan stir together the flour, mustard, bouillon granules, pepper and nutmeg.
Gradually stir in the milk until smooth.
Stir in the water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the chicken or turkey, Swiss cheese and wine.
Pour the sauce over the broccoli.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with the green onion or parsley.
Makes 4 servings.
Total calories per serving 225.
Total fat grams per serving 7 grams.

title: stained glass candy
directions: *Such
as
peppermint, cinnamon, cloves, wintergreen or sassafras.	Buy at drugstore.

title: 20 minute pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixer and beat for 20 minutes at high speed.
Pour into greased tube or loaf pan.
Put into a cold oven and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Scald milk, then add to mixture.
Boil 10 minutes.
Blend eggs in blender or use electric mixer until soft peaks.
Add part of eggs to custard slowly to prevent curdling.
Mix well, then add rest of eggs.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Chill, then add cream, half and half and vanilla.
Add treats, then put in ice cream freezer.
Delicious!

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Any fresh fruit can be used.
Thread an assortment of fruit on each skewer with a strawberry at the top.
Chill.
For a fancy table centerpiece, insert one end of each kabob on the outside of the empty watermelon rind half.
Fill in empty spaces by placing grapes, berries or pineapple chunks onto toothpicks and insert into rind.
Serves 48 kabobs.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Toss sausage with cheese and bread pieces.
Put in 8-inch Pyrex casserole.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diane's veal stew
directions: Saute onion, bacon, celery, chopped olives and herbs until soft.
Remove from pan and saute meat until lightly browned all over.
Return all ingredients to heavy casserole and sprinkle with the flour.
Add all the ingredients except the mushrooms, artichokes and pitted olives.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
If there is not enough chicken broth to just cover ingredients, add some extra water.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms and artichokes in 2 tablespoons of butter lightly and add to stew when done.
At this time, add the pitted olives.
Stir and simmer for about 10
more minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: sun tea
directions: Put tea bags in a clean gallon jar and fill with cold water. Cap loosely.
Place in hot sunshine for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove tea bags.
Sweeten to taste; serve over ice.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; then pour in ginger ale.
Makes one punch bowl full.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix together ingredients; chill.
Spread on Triscuits crackers and top with a dab of cocktail sauce.

title: pork goulash(gulasz wieprzowy)
directions: Use cheaper cuts of meat.
Have butcher bone and cut meat into serving pieces.
Combine in heavy casserole the meat, onions, seasoning and paprika and simmer, tightly covered, turning occasionally, until meat browns.
Dust with flour and add soup stock, tomato puree and the parboiled potatoes.
Cover and continue to simmer until meat and potatoes are done, about 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut up chicken in cube-size pieces.
Heat wok or frying pan until a drop of water rolls like a ball.
Add oil.
Add chicken and ginger root.
Stir-fry until chicken turns white.
Add teriyaki sauce and juice from canned pineapple.
Stir until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and add pineapple and almonds.
Cook another 3 minutes.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use with grilled meats or serve as salsa dip with chips.
I put more onions and tomatoes than it calls for.

title: cheddar cheese pennies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Using food processor, shred cheese. Position knife blade in processor bowl and then add shredded cheese, flour, butter or margarine and dry mustard.
Process until mixture forms a ball.
Remove knife blade.

title: cory's chix adobo
directions: Cut up a whole chicken or equivalent parts of same.
Place spread out in a slow cooker.
Cover with the remaining ingredients and cook for 6 to 8 hours.
The sauce and spices may be adjusted to taste.
When done, serve over rice.

title: greek salad supper
directions: In large bowl, mix lettuce (iceberg and romaine), radishes, onion, Feta cheese, tomatoes, anchovies, olives and cucumbers. Cover and chill.
In separate bowl, beat oil with vinegar, salt, pepper, oregano and sugar until thick.
Let stand at room temperature.
Before serving, beat dressing again and pour over salad.
Serve with Cheese Pita Breads.
Slash pita breads at one side and stuff each with Mozzarella cheese. Place pitas in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Boil syrup, water and sugar until stiff threads form or to 260°.
Beat until stiff.
Pour syrup slowly into egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Add coconut, nuts or fruit and mix.
Shape into eggs.
When cold, coat with chocolate.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin in double boiler.
Drop eggs into chocolate mixture to coat.
Remove from chocolate with two forks. Place on wax paper to cool.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks; add ice cream and milk.
Slowly add bourbon, rum and brandy.
Beat egg whites and fold in carefully.
Serve with nutmeg.
Makes 10 servings.

title: ham 'n cheese chowder
directions: Place 1/2 cup of water and salt in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and reduce heat.
Cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain potatoes, reserving liquid; set aside. Melt butter in a 3-quart Dutch oven; add onion and saute until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Stir in milk and potato liquid and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add potatoes and ham.
Heat gently.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Top with croutons.

title: special chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken in pressure pot 30 minutes at 10 pounds pressure. Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Mix chicken broth with cornstarch and Worcestershire sauce. Add to onion and green pepper mixture.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pull chicken off bone and add to sauce mixture. Add tomatoes. Simmer for 35 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cajun jambalaya
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in oil in large skillet over medium heat. Remove chicken and set aside.
Pour off fat.
Return 1 tablespoon fat to skillet; add celery, onions, pepper and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add flour; stir.
Add rice, seasonings, broth and Worcestershire.
Place chicken pieces in skillet.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Serve with hot pepper sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together 1 stick butter, mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, vanilla, eggs and milk.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix the brown sugar, nuts, flour and 1/3 cup butter.
Layer on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: beef and zucchini
directions: Heat oil
in
skillet, add onions and garlic and saute. Add meat
and
cook
through.
Add zucchini, oregano, salt and pepper (zucchini
should be tender, but crisp).
Add tomatoes last and just
heat
through.
Sprinkle
all with parsley and lemon juice and toss gently.
Serve with rice.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Tear angel food cake apart after you cook it. Put in long pan 1 layer of angel food cake. Then put layer of strawberries, 1 whole package. Just spread over cake. Then add 1 layer of whip cream over strawberries. Then repeat. On top of cake over the whip cream, spread the strawberry glaze. There you have Strawberry Surprise.

title: fruit salad
directions: Soak bananas in orange juice to prevent discoloration. Combine remaining fruit and marshmallows.
Stir in sour cream. Drain liquid from bananas and add to mixture.

title: 7 layer cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cracker crumbs; press down.
Put coconut over top of this, then start layering all the rest, using Eagle Brand last.
Pour it evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg until well blended. Stir in milk, lemon extract and vinegar.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture until stiff dough forms.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 425° or until apples are tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and brown sugar.
Mix in eggs. Combine flour, salt, soda and oats and add to mixture.
Blend in peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: poached fish with horseradish sauce
directions: Bring 2 cups lightly salted water just to boiling.
Add fish. Return to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer until fish flakes easily (about 6 minutes).
Stir together dip and horseradish and serve over fish.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken, rice, soup, mayonnaise, chestnuts, almonds, onions, salt and pepper.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart ungreased dish. Combine 1 tablespoon melted butter and cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: magic peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well; roll mixture into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross by dipping fork into water and pressing on cookie balls.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until desired brownness.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer until slightly thickened. Chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Let butter stand to room temperature.
Beat butter until soft and add sugar.
Add eggs alternately with portions of flour.
Add vanilla and mix slightly.
Place in an ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, enchilada sauce and soup and simmer.
Tear tortillas and line pan with pieces. Put layer of meat, onion, then cheese; repeat layers.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, fat, corn, green pepper and seasoning. Pour into greased baking dish.
Set dish in pan of hot water. Bake until firm, about an hour.

title: hamburger meatballs
directions: Mix all together, make into meatballs.
Brown in skillet on all sides.
Drain all fat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk. Cook on low for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cheap meal with potatoes and veggies.

title: chicken marinated
directions: In small pot, heat together water, butter, onion, steak sauce, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken breasts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: world's best banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and butter together.
Add other ingredients in their respective order.
The flour, salt and soda should be sifted together.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300° in a regular size loaf pan (greased and floured).
Yields 1 large loaf.

title: old fashioned pecan cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs for 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma clifford's sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla, nutmeg and orange rind.
Beat until fluffy.
Add 2 cups flour, then buttermilk, then 2 cups flour.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll out to about 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut in 3-inch rounds and sprinkle with granulated sugar and dot with a raisin.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: upside-down dutch apple cake
directions: Place apples in greased pie plate; cover with cinnamon and sugar.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour, shortening and vanilla in a bowl, then pour over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar again. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fluff
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 2 hours, then serve.
Crushed nuts are optional.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Add the soda; stir. Do not drain off water, as that is your liquid.
Let cool.
Cream shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Add 1 cup flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg, then add remaining 3 cups flour, vanilla and nuts.
To the dough, add a pinch of cloves and a pinch of allspice.
Add the dates, candied cherries and pineapple.
Mix fruit with another 1/2 cup flour; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 275° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 10 dozen.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup granulated sugar, 3 teaspoons cinnamon and chopped nuts, if desired.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the mixture over the batter.
Pour the other half of the batter over this.
Sprinkle other half and swirl with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange bread cubes in greased 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine milk, egg, salt and mustard.
Pour over other.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: green chili chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken stock and soup in a large pan over medium heat, stirring until well blended.
Slowly add whipping cream and sour cream; stir well.
Add chicken, chillies and jalapenos.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: alberta's dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan, empty crushed pineapple and juice.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Add cherry pie filling. Spread dry cake mix over top of cherries.
Cut butter over top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, sugar and egg in large bowl; beat until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookies will appear uncooked when first removed from oven.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey, add onion and pepper. Add other ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes or until desired temp.

title: sugar-free bread pudding
directions: Cook and serve pudding mix with milk as directed on package. Add vanilla, butter, and raisins if desired.
Serve with Dream Whip.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all together and pour in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until cake rises, then flops.
Very good!

title: trudy's white cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into two small balls, then roll in finely chopped pecans or place on a large platter and serve with crackers, surrounding it with fresh parsley sprigs.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix and add to macaroni.
Let refrigerate overnight.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs, milk and bread crumbs.
In a large skillet heat 1 tablespoon of butter.
Saute onions until soft, about 5 minutes.
Lift out with slotted spoon.
Add to bread crumbs, along with meat, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, allspice, nutmeg and cardamom.
Mix well.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.
Shape into meatballs, about 1-inch diameter.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Cover, shake and store 2 days.

title: pork and veal noodles
directions: Brown the pork and beef or veal in small amount of oil. Season and put in large roaster or kettle.
Add the celery, cream of chicken soup, 2 cans water and the dry onion soup mix.
Cook in oven at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add the dry noodles, cooked in consomme and water.
Add the mushrooms.
Cook until well blended. Serves 12.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix fat and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) about 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: english trifle
directions: Split ladyfingers in two (or split sponge cake in two and cut one layer in sections the size of ladyfingers (12 sections). Arrange in single layer in bottom of square glass baking dish, 9 x 9 x 1 1/2 inch.
Make jello as instructed on box.
Pour over the ladyfingers.
Allow to set.

title: green chili salsa
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, place tomatoes, chili peppers, onion, garlic and hot pepper sauce, if desired. Cover and blend or process about 5 seconds or until combined, but still chunky.
Serve at room temperature or transfer to a small saucepan and heat just until warm.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour batter in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spareribs hawaiian style(6 servings)
directions: Cut ribs in serving pieces.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir in vinegar, catsup, undrained pineapple and soy sauce. Cook until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Arrange ribs in roasting pan.
Cover with pineapple mixture.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes. Heat 2 cups water, sugar and shortening in a saucepan until shortening melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add yeast mixture, eggs, salt and 1 cup flour, mixing well.
Gradually stir in remaining flour (dough will be soft).
Place dough in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: cauliflower ham casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk and add cauliflower, bread cubes, ham, celery and chopped pimento.
Mix together and put in casserole. Top with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serves 6.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Beat together eggs, sour cream, water and oil in large bowl until thoroughly mixed.
Add cake mix and pudding mix.
Pour into buttered Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: fruit juicy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, pouring ginger ale and Sprite in last along with the ice cream.

title: alaska hotcakes
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together 3 times.
Mix the flour mixture with water and beat thoroughly.
Then add Wesson oil and yolks of eggs.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites very stiff, fold into batter and then add baking powder.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix well.
Spread over crust immediately.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool. Cut into small squares or bars.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix in order given (can use blender).
Spoon in small amounts on hot (380° to 400°) buttered griddle.
For larger cakes, tip and turn griddle so batter runs all over pan.
Add extra butter or margarine on pan as needed.

title: california casserole
directions: Saute cut up squash and onion in oil until tender, but still firm.
Add corn and picante sauce.
Heat until hot.
Pour into serving bowl; add cheese to the top.
Serve.

title: jeff's beef stew
directions: Cut beef roast into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place cubes in skillet with 3 tablespoons of butter or margarine until brown.
Add the beef seasoning and Open Pit barbecue sauce while browning your meat.
Once meat is browned, place in a crock-pot with water, potatoes, carrots and celery.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 hours.
Add mushrooms and tortellini the last 40 minutes of cooking time.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and mix well. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk and yeast.
Knead slightly, then cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before using. Use as needed.
You may keep dough covered in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: snow flakes(child's recipe)
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in large microwaveable bowl on Medium (50%) for 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir in flakes until all are well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let set until hard.

title: whole wheat crisps
directions: Sift the
flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the sugar and mix to
a
stiff dough with the cream.
Roll very thin and cut out with
biscuit
cutter.
Bake
in
hot oven on greased cookie sheet.

title: slippery pancakes
directions: Mix and let set few minutes.
If thinner pancakes are desired, add more milk.
We find the thinner, the better.
Make pan hot, 380° or more.
Serve with real maple syrup.
Makes 8 pancakes.

title: fudge sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Blend in water, stirring until cocoa is dissolved.
Add milk; bring to boiling. Boil gently 3 to 4 minutes until sauce thickens, constantly stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Makes 1 cup sauce.
Serve warm or cold.
Delicious over pound cake and/or ice cream.

title: impossible pie
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender.
Blend 20 seconds.
Pour into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° if glass pan, 350° if metal, for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: salmon with onions & capers
directions: Preheat oven to 350° F. In a non-stick 12-inch skillet, heat 1 tsp. olive oil over medium high heat until hot.
Add salmon rounded side down and cook until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Transfer salmon to 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In the same skillet, add remaining 1 tsp. oil, cook onion over medium heat 5 minutes or until tender.
Add capers, vinegar and sugar and cook 2 minutes stirring constantly.
Spoon caper mixture over salmon, cover with foil and place in the oven. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until salmon flakes easily.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix creamer, flour, salt, paprika, garlic powder, pepper and onion.
Put
cup
potatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/3
of
the nondairy creamer mixture and dot with 1/3 of the butter.
Repeat.
Pour
boiling water over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter small casserole dish. Pour into dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: After melting margarine in microwave, add next six ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350 degrees for exactly 30 minutes.
Serve warm
with vanilla ice cream.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Toss cooked macaroni and 2 tablespoons oil well.
Add all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour all ingredients into lightly greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 5 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: so-o-o good cookie clusters
directions: Heat white chocolate over low heat until just melted.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Drop on wax paper and let harden.
Enjoy!

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: While fettuccine cooks, place next 7 ingredients, in order given, in a food processor with steel blade.
Quickly turn machine on and off until mixture combines.
With motor running, add oil in a thin stream.
Add cheese and butter, blending until mixture has a uniform consistency.
Add approximately 1/4 cup warm water to pesto to thin slightly and spoon over pasta.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and cut off ends.
Boil in salted water for 10 minutes.
Cool and scoop out zucchini insides.
Saute onions, add meat and mushrooms and seasonings.
Brown mixture, drain off fat. Remove from heat.
Add zucchini insides and 2 to 3 ounces of Parmesan cheese.
Fill the zucchini shells with this mixture.
Put in baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be cheese of your choice to top, if desired.

title: canned vegetable soup
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Add water to cover and cook for 1 hour. Add 1 gallon cut up tomatoes and simmer for 1 hour.
Fill jars and seal.
When serving, cook a soup bone or boil ribs and add a jar of vegetables and cooked noodles.

title: no added fat cake
directions: While mixing cake, substitute 4 egg whites instead of whole eggs or use egg substitute.
Substitute equivalent applesauce instead of oil.
Follow baking directions as on package.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinade chicken 1 hour with Dales and water.
Salt with season salt before grilling.
Cook chicken on grill till done. Before removing, brush chicken with 1/2 glaze and 1/2 honey mix. Leave on grill for an additional 10 minutes after brushing.

title: mom's potato pancakes
directions: Shred potatoes.
Mix all ingredients well.
In skillet, heat 1/4-inch oil over medium heat.
Drop batter by 1/3 cup in hot oil. Flatten to form pancake.
Fry until golden brown on both sides; drain on paper towel.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roseville lemon cake
directions: Lightly oil or spray a 12 cup Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine the cake mix and lemon pudding.

title: cracker pizza
directions: Put crackers on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cheese on crackers and place pepperoni on top.
Cook just long enough for the cheese to begin to melt.

title: chews
directions: Beat eggs; add brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Mix and add nuts. Pour into 10 x 12-inch flat, well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Allow to cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Put chicken, pineapple, celery, pecans and 1/2 sour cream mixture in pie crust and top with other half sour cream mix.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and a sprinkle of chopped olives.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake until bubbly at 350°, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles and buttered crumbs. Alternate layers in greased 2-quart baking dish with noodles.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake until heated through at 375°, 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and soup. Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Pour off marinade and reserve half.
Bake wings at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain. Pour reserved marinade over wings and bake additional 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: dathyl's chicken ole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place chicken breasts.
Mix soup, chilies and mushroom pieces.
Spread over chicken breasts.
Cover with Saran Wrap then aluminum foil.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Uncover and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serve with chicken rice or egg noodles, green vegetable and warm flour tortillas.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Stir
in milk, blueberries and oil.	Pour in dry ingredients
all
at
once	and
stir
just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups about
3/4 full.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400° or until golden
brown.
Remove
from	pan
immediately.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: salad or dessert
directions: Mix and freeze.
Remove from freezer in time to soften just a little before serving.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and butter or margarine.
Then add powdered sugar, crushed pineapple and vanilla.
Put icing on cake and sprinkle with coconut.

title: russian winter tea
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Keep in a tight lid container.
Place 3 to 4 teaspoons of powdered mix in an 8-ounce cup of hot water.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool and beat.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: basil grilled chicken
directions: Press coarsely ground pepper into meaty side of chicken breasts.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush on chicken. Brill chicken over medium coals for 8 to 10 minutes on each side, basting frequently with remaining butter mixture.
May be baked in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: spatzle
directions: Stir together flour and salt in bowl.
Blend egg and milk. Stir into flour mixture.
Place half the dough in 1-quart strainer.
Hold over soup kettle of boiling water.
With rubber spatula, press dough through strainer to form spatzle.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Drain.
Melt 4 tablespoons of margarine and mix in spatzles.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with remaining pie crust.
Crimp edges.
Cut slits into top crust and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain
last 4 ingredients.
Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cool.
Combine vegetables.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally.
Let stand 12 hours.

title: grandma stone's corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Spray pan with Pam or unsalted shortening.
I use iron skillet.
Bake at 450° to 500° until brown and firm.

title: beet pickles
directions: Leave root and 1-inch of stem on beets.
Scrub well with vegetable brush.
Place beets in saucepan and add enough water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook 35 to 40 minutes or until tender; drain.
Pour cold water over beets and drain again.
Let cool.
Trim off beet stem and roots and rub off skins.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter or oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar together; press into a pan.
Press up on sides a little.
Combine and bake 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onions with beef.
Drain.
Mix eggs in separate bowl.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Mix eggs and ground beef together.
Pour into pie shell.
Add milk and cheeses.
Top with bacon.
Cook on 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add cheese to top.
Enjoy!

title: luau barbecued ribs
directions: In 1-quart pan, melt butter.
Saute onions until tender.
Blend in sugar, salt, chili powder and mustard.
Stir in pineapple juice, lemon juice, catsup and chili, soy and A.1. sauces.
Heat to boiling, lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Mix it all together and drink it with a medium diet Coke.
I like diet Coke.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 375° oven, stirring occasionally, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter into three 9-inch prepared cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix yolks and milk, then add lime juice.
Pour into crust. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add the topping.
Easy and delicious.

title: corn casserole
directions: Oven 350°, drain corn.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour in whipping cream.
Stir in flour.
Cut butter in small pieces and put on top of mixture.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute okra in oleo until tender, adding remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Very gradually add milk mixture to eggs stirring until well blended.
Add extract.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake on center shelf of preheated oven at 450° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 to 20 minutes or until center is firm.
For a change, coconut may be sprinkled over crust before filling is added.

title: christmas breakfast grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Bring milk and water to boil.
Add grits, stirring.
Simmer until grits are done, 2 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, but remove pan from heat first.
Pour into buttered dish and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until top is lightly browned.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix well. Pour over rhubarb and strawberries. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal
directions: Combine in bowl; cook in a microwave for 2 minutes.
When finished, stir and cover for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix pie filling according to package directions.
Spread on next.
Then top with Cool Whip and pecan chips.

title: moroccan-style salmon
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in a medium skillet over medium heat until golden.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato liquid, honey, lemon rind and cumin.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and season with salt, pepper and cayenne to taste.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple.
Melt margarine in cast iron skillet (9 or 10 inch).
Remove from heat, add brown sugar and stir until blended.
Arrange pineapple slices in skillet.
Place 1 cherry in center of each slice.
Spread prepared cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Let stand in skillet 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: marinated glazed chicken
directions: In a small bowl, thoroughly blend all ingredients except chicken.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in a shallow pan, skin side up.
Pour dressing over chicken and marinate overnight. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting every half hour.
May be frozen and reheated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Beat margarine; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat again.
Add vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Beat until blended.
Fold in milk, alternating with flour.
Fold in berries. Scoop batter into muffin cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar (or nutmeg sugar) and bake at 375° until golden for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool before removing.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Brown meat and onion; add tomato sauce, water, sugar and seasonings.
Combine beans and meat mixture. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated. Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, chicken and green beans.
Add mayonnaise and soup. Top with can of onion rings.

title: cocktail sauce for shrimp
directions: Make Sauce:
Combine chili sauce, ketchup and horseradish to taste, at least 1 tablespoon.
Keep adding horseradish until you get the right amount of "zip!"
Add juice from about 1/6 lemon. Mix thoroughly and chill for several hours.
Mince celery and green onion.
Store separately in the refrigerator to crisp.
When ready to serve, fill cocktail glasses or wine glasses with bay shrimp. (The amount of shrimp you will need will depend on the size of your serving glass.)
Sprinkle shrimp with a little celery and green onion.
Top with cocktail sauce.
Add a squeeze of lemon and garnish with lemon wedge.
Offer extra sauce at table.
Omit celery and onion to use as a dip for large (peel and eat type) shrimp.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add onion and saute.
Put uncooked rice into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour consomme and bouillon over rice; stir in onion and margarine.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and let refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: lemon-herb grilled chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch rectangular dish. Shake remaining ingredients in tightly covered container; pour over chicken.
Turn chicken to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: reservations
directions: Look up the phone number of your favorite restaurant in the phone book.
Pick up the receiver of your telephone and dial the phone number. If they answer, I'm sure they will accommodate you.

title: biscuit fan tans
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir water into Bisquick to make a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board; knead 5 times.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Spread half soft butter over half the dough; fold over and spread remaining butter over other half of dough.
Fold in half; roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a floured 2-inch cutter.
Place 2 biscuits, cut side up, in each ungreased muffin cup.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 9 biscuits.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender. Drain beef and onion well.
Add rest of ingredients and let simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This can be served over rice to make it go farther, but it does make a large pan full.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until soft.
Gradually add flour and oats.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Drop by spoon. Cook 8 to 10 to 12 minutes at 325°, until golden brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg; add corn, seasonings, flour and milk.
Bake at 300° for one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 8 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter bits and marshmallow cream. Beat this until smooth and thick. Pour into an 8 x 8 greased baking dish. Let cool before cutting.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Add pineapple, bananas, nuts and strawberries.
Pour half of mixture in pan and congeal until firm.
Cover with sour cream.
Put other half of mixture on top.
Chill.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: nancy sherman's hot green pepper jelly
directions: You will need small jelly jars, sterilized and hot.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Let sit for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture and beat.
Add vanilla; mix grated carrots, walnuts, flaked coconut and crushed pineapple.
Add to mixture; blend well.
Pour batter in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes clean.
Cool on cake rack.
Remove from pan.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over dates.
Stir in soda to remaining 1/2 cup water.
Mix soda water, dates and flour and nuts together.
Cream sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla and add to previous ingredients.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for about 1 hour (check with toothpick in middle).
Take out of pans immediately.
Cool.
Serve with cream cheese mixed with 1 tablespoon of raspberry jam as spread.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown the pork chops and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients, reserving 1/2 c. cheese and half of the onion rings. Spoon into a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Arrange pork chops on top of the potato mixture and cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings and bake uncovered 5 more minutes.
Serves 4-6.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 11 inch pan with wax paper.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, cinnamon and eggs; mix well and pour into bottom of prepared pan.
sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture, covering completely.
Put nuts evenly over dry mixture. Pour butter over all and bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.
Invert onto tray.
Remove wax paper.
Make sure crisp is cool before frosting.

title: shapiro's chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the crushed graham crackers and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted butter. Press the mixture into the bottom and 2 inches up the sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 10 minutes.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk; stir in dried beef, onion, green peppers and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.
Plan to make a double batch; one won't be enough.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix
with
carrots, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix and add sour cream and chicken soup. Add pimentos.
Melt oleo;
add
to
mixture
with
cornbread stuffing.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carnation dish
directions: Fry onions and pepper in margarine until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients in pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; turn oven off and leave 1 hour to linger.

title: meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Make mixture into small balls; fry until done.

title: tasty rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Put in bottom of casserole dish. Add rice.
Mix beef broth and consomme.
Pour over rice and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pasta with sausage(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute sliced sausage into rounds; remove from pan.
Discard fat.
Melt butter; saute sliced green and red peppers and onions. Do not brown.
Blend in flour and gradually add milk.
Cook almost to a boil.
Add cheeses to melt.
Place cooked pasta, sausage and sauce into large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sauteed mushrooms can also be added.
Easily doubles.

title: glazed onions
directions: Put the onions in a saucepan; add the other ingredients and mix well.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes or until the onions are tender and the sauce is almost absorbed, stirring a few times. Serves 6.
Each serving contains 40 calories.

title: lo-cal maple syrup
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling and sugar substitute.
Blend well and add maple flavoring.

title: crockpot hamburger stew
directions: Put layers of vegetables in order above in crockpot. Season each layer with salt & pepper. Then put browned hamburger on top of celery. Mix tomato soup & 1 can of water together & pour over hamburger. Cover and cook on high for 2-4 hours, stir on occasion. May add 1 can beef gravy (optional) after mixture has cooked awhile.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add Mountain Dew and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Mix together milk and pudding, then mix in
the Cool Whip.
Spread on top of Jell-O.

title: corn oyster casserole
directions: Cook corn and season to taste.
Put layer of corn in casserole dish; top with layer of oysters.
Top with layer of cracker crumbs. Dot with butter.
Make another layer of corn, oysters and cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Pour milk over all until all ingredients are covered.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown, about 1 hour. Very good.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in a bowl.
Spread this into the bottom of a cake pan (9x13), let cool.
Beat 1 cup sugar with the cream cheese.
Fold in the cool whip.
Spread mixture on top of pretzels.
Combine jello, boiling water, frozen berries together and place in refrigerator.
Once it starts to set pour this over the cream cheese layer.
Return to refrigerator until chilled and set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine the chicken broth, lentils, onions, brown rice, basil, salt, oregano, thyme, garlic and black pepper in a large saucepan with tight-fitting lid.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until the lentils and rice are tender, the liquid absorbed.
Stir in cheese last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make crisscross with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave 3 minute fudge
directions: Put all ingredients, except the nuts, in a glass dish or microwave-safe dish.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave. Quickly stir until smooth.
Add nuts and pour into pan to cool.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine.
Add sugar, dates and egg; mix well.
Bring to a boil on medium heat and boil about 4 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Mix and set aside to cool.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: mac-n-cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Make macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Mix all together and eat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve pudding mix with a portion of juice from the pineapple.
Should be fairly thick.
Mix in fruit.

title: baked german carp fish
directions: Combine ingredients for dressing.
Place dressing in pan lined with foil.
Place fish on top of dressing.
Salt and pepper fish. Cut onion slices and place on top of fish.
Put a pat of butter on each onion slice.
Cook for 1 hour in a 450° oven.

title: tuna and potato chip casserole
directions: Combine tuna, soup, and milk. Saute celery and onion in margarine and add to mixture. Crush enough potato chips to thicken mixture. Pour into a casserole dish and add a layer of crushed chips on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Slice potatoes medium thin and parboil about 5 minutes.
Add celery for 3 minutes more.
In greased baking pan, place 1 layer of potatoes, ham, celery and onion (drain potatoes and celery). Cover with soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Pour remaining soup over all.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes until brown.

title: cool casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers. Drain and add all other ingredients. Top with cheese slices. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: lemon fruit dip
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until it thickens.
Add miniature marshmallows and stir until dissolved. Great served with grapes.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, then soda, flour, salt, sour cream and almond flavoring.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cranberry sauce, then add remaining batter. Top with remaining cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool frost with:

title: cauliflower-broccoli mix
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add crushed crackers and mix well; set aside.
Cook frozen vegetables until tender and drain.
Melt Cheez Whiz.
Add canned milk and 1/2 stick of margarine; set aside.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and flour; blend thoroughly. Turn onto pastry cloth, which has 1/4 cup flour on it.
Knead dough lightly for 1 minute.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Use fairly large skillet.
Place cheese over hamburger.
Sprinkle celery over top.
Add olives, then noodles.
Pour tomatoes and water over all.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce(serves 8)
directions: Brown hamburger, garlic, onion and green pepper (drain fat). After browned, add, in large kettle, spices, tomato products, brown sugar, vinegar and meat mixture.
Simmer together one hour. Add Parmesan or shredded Monterey Jack cheese to taste.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine ingredients and make into balls.
Deep fry.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green lima bean bake
directions: Cook beans until almost done.
Pour boiling water over broccoli cuts and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain both.
Mix other ingredients with vegetables and place in well-greased casserole. Top with herb stuffing crumbs and 2 tablespoons of oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Beat egg white and cold water until foamy, not stiff.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip pecan halves in egg white, then in sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: maddie's cookies
directions: Sift together flour and spices; set aside.
Cream together sugar and margarine; add molasses and egg.
In a small bowl, mix baking soda, water and vinegar.
Alternate adding flour and liquid to creamed mixture.
Chill dough and form balls; roll in additional sugar.
Bake on greased sheets at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rice-green chili casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine cooked rice and sour cream; mix well.
Layer in well buttered baking dish the following:
1/2 rice mixture, green chilies and Cheddar cheese.
Top with the remaining rice mixture and Parmesan cheese. Dot with butter and sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and orange peel; set aside.
In small bowl mix sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Slowly combine dry mixture to wet mixture, blend well.
Drop onto
ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 4 to 5 minutes or until done (top of cookie will spring back when touched).
Let cool, then frost.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Drain clams and save juice.
Melt butter and blend in flour and mustard.
Add milk and 2/3 cup clam juice, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add pepper, oregano, onion and cheese.
Remove from heat.
Stir to melt cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, clams, parsley and bread crumbs.
Chill mixture.
Fill shells.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Dip chicken into melted margarine.
Roll in Parmesan cheese and bread crumb mixture. Place chicken into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Do not cover while baking.

title: oma's linzer torte
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter with pastry cutter or knife until butter resembles fine pebbles.
Mix milk with beaten eggs and add to flour and butter mixture.
Mix and knead until batter forms a ball.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
(Wrap in plastic or wax paper.)

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Line pan with melted butter and brown sugar.
Also, on top of butter, put honey or molasses.
Add water to mixture.
Put pieces into pan.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350°.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix cranberries, dressing and soup mix and pour over chicken. Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix beans and onion together.
Mix other ingredients and pour over beans.
Refrigerate overnight.
