title: crunch salad
directions: Rinse and drain lettuce.
Pat dry and chill to crisp.
Chop lettuce and toss with onions.
In small bowl, combine noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Sprinkle noodle mixture over lettuce and onions.
Add dressing and toss.
Best when served immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: After mixing the cheese and sugar, add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Later blend in the Cool Whip.
Pour into flat pan (9 x 13-inch) or a molded bowl.
Freeze.
This keeps well.
You may take this out 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in milk.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves about 14.

title: brussels sprouts casserole
directions: Cook sprouts in 1/2 cup water until tender; drain.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut in half.
Mix these two together and place in buttered casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread over top.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package.
Let cool.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to directions.
Break candy bars into tiny pieces.
Break up half the brownies into small pieces and place in bottom of large glass bowl.
Cover with half the mousse, then half the candy, then half the whipped topping.
Repeat layers. Feeds up to 24 (or one serious chocoholic!).

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon; add eggs.
Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture with dry ingredients and creamed mix.
Stir in nuts. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: butter cream torte
directions: Spread evenly 1 cup of the crumbs, in a 9-inch pie plate or square pan.
Cream butter and add eggs and sugar.
Beat until fluffy and light (separation is normal).
Stir in almonds.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup crumbs over butter mixture. Beat cream until thick.
Add cherries which have been well drained and chopped.
Mix well and add to second layer crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Garnish with whole cherries. Chill at least 4 hours.
Can be frozen.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Prepare fruit however you would like it.
After you have prepared, pour the lemon pudding over the top and stir it until it is dissolved.

title: cheesy chiches
directions: Grease four (10 ounce)) custard cups with butter.
Cut 2 of biscuits into 8 pie shaped wedges each.
Roll remaining biscuits into 4 to 5-inch circles.
Place one in each cup pressing against bottom and up the sides.

title: charlie's delights
directions: Line bottom of 10 x 15 cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.
Mix together 1 cup margarine, sugar, milk and egg. Bring ingredients to a full boil and remove from heat.
Add graham cracker crumbs, walnuts or pecans and coconut.
Spread mixture over graham crackers; cover with second layer of Honey Graham crackers.
Mix together 1/2 cup margarine, powdered sugar and juice of one lemon.
Spread mixture over honey grahams.
Cover; refrigerate and let stand overnight.
Cut into small bar shapes. Bars may be frozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Prepare rice with broth until tender and broth is gone.
Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, rice, 1/2 chicken, broccoli and 1/2 chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice to make sauce.
Pour over layers.
Top with 2 cups cornflake crumbs, mixed with 1/2 stick margarine, melted.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is absorbed.
Mash raisins. Add eggs, oil, applesauce, vanilla and sweetener.
Add dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Exchange:
1 bread, 1 fat and 1/2 fruit.

title: favorite beef loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Shape mixture in a loaf in shallow baking dish.
Press two green pepper rings and an onion ring atop meat loaf, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serves 6-8.

title: cranberry mandarin salad
directions: Combine gelatin and cranberry sauce in saucepan over medium heat; heat and stir until almost boiling and gelatin is dissolved. Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts, mandarin oranges, undrained pineapple and ginger ale.
When sizzling stops, pour mixture into oiled 5-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Serves 8.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Roll nuts, candy, and dates in a little extra flour.
Add coconut to the floured mixture and roll all this to batter.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Pour topping over cake while it is still warm.
Let set 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: grandmother's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add chocolate mixture.
Stir well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in greased, glass baking dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips together in double boiler and add can of chow mein noodles.
Stir until well coated and drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Let get firm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream together sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 1/2 stick oleo, milk and vanilla (using mixer).
Put in a large buttered casserole.

title: strawberry layer cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Place in a 9 x
13 inch pan. Sprinkle pudding over cake.
Mix strawberries and glaze together. Pour mixture over pudding and cake pieces.
Top with whipped topping.

title: meat loaf
directions: Thaw or defrost meat.
Chop and measure all ingredients into large pot.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cut fat off pork chops.
Brown in skillet.
Bring to boil the liquid ingredients and pour over pork chops, pepper and onion rings in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender, drain. Saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender, add soup and mix.
Add cheese, heat and stir until melted.
Remove.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper in ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter.
Cook
and stir crumbs in butter until browned, sprinkling over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread in order in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° about one hour.
Easy and always a tasty favorite!

title: potato-cheese bake
directions: Mix together ingredients except corn flakes and margarine.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch greased casserole or cake pan.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Dot with 1 stick margarine.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler over hot water melt white chocolate.
Fold in nuts and cheese mixture.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish that is lined with waxed paper.
Chill.
Lift out of dish by paper and cut. Smooth and creamy and delicious.

title: monsetti
directions: Cook noodles for 5 minutes; drain.
Brown beef; drain. Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Cover; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove cover; continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Beat the egg well.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Beat until fluffy.
Add milk and the corn.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain two cans green peas.
Add boiled eggs, onion, pickles, salt and pepper.
Mix with mayo and a little mustard.

title: ida's special rice krispie bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil, but don't continue to boil.
Add and mix well, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in a
9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt butterscotch bits and chocolate bits and spread on top of bars.
Refrigerate to cool. Cut in squares.
Does not require refrigeration after topping is set.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and wine together and beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add poppy seeds and stir until blended.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: my favorite salsa
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Can be made ahead of time as long as you refrigerate it.

title: lord baltimore cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar on high speed.
Beat egg yolks into this mixture one at a time.
Put baking soda into the milk.
Beat flour alternating with milk and add the rest of the flavorings. Put in layer pans and bake about 25 minutes or put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: kolaches
directions: Pour
cup
lukewarm
water over yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar,
let
stand
minutes then add 1 cup lukewarm milk, again let stand 5 minutes then add 1 1/2 cups flour and let
rise a
little.
Add
eggs,
cup sugar, salt, 1 cup lukewarm milk, butter, lard, cream and 4 1/4 cups flour.
Mix with
wooden spoon until smooth.
Let rise.
Mix down and let rise
until double.
Then dip out by a tablespoon on a floured board
and roll in palm of your hands into a nice ball.
Place on
greased
cookie sheet and brush with butter.
Let rise and press
center
down and fill with stewed fruit, prunes, apricots,
peaches, or cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with topping made of
cup
flour,
cup sugar
and about 2 tablespoons butter.
Let rise and bake at 375°.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together ingredients in the order given. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, stir together broth, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth; stir in ham, snow peas and onions.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes or until boiling, stirring twice during cooking.

title: shirley and kim's tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine ingredients in large bowl, except Tater Tots.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour ingredients in a glass dish.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine the ingredients and cook about 5 minutes until thick. Pour into a baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/4 cups servings.
Exchanges: 3 meat, 1 1/2 bread, 1 vegetable and 1/2 fat.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute the celery and onions in butter until tender.
The sage, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper are all to taste.
If too moist, add saltine crackers (about 12); if too dry, add more stock (or chicken broth).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Boil together for five minutes the sugar and water.
Add tea leaves and steep five minutes.
Cool this mixture; add the juices. Just before serving, add ginger ale (chilled).

title: fudge
directions: Mix together.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil slowly until a few drops form a ball when dropped in water.
Cool. Add 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat until it shapes.
Pour into greased pan.
Press at once into top 3 dozen almonds or walnuts.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Boil potatoes and onion about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients and bake in long Pyrex dish about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: josephine's white bread stuffing
directions: Warm milk, melting margarine in the milk.
Mix bread, celery, onion, salt and sage together.
Add two eggs and then add in milk mixture.
Stuff in turkey and cook along with turkey or cook separately in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: egg souffle casserole
directions: Cut each sausage link into 4 pieces.
Cook in a large skillet until brown; drain and set aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
In a medium casserole layer:
noodles, meat and onion mixture.
Cover with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add strawberries.
Stir and refrigerate until thickened.
Add mashed bananas, nuts and pineapple and stir.
Pour half of the mixture in bowl and put sour cream on top.
Then add the rest of jello mixture over the sour cream.
Refrigerate.

title: baked ziti
directions: Boil ziti; in mixing bowl combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and spices.
In baking dish, combine ziti, sauce and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese generously on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Add to potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and oil together; add remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls; place about 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: champagne risotto
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in butter until onion is soft. Add rice and stir, making sure each grain is coated with butter. Increase heat to medium and add champagne.
Stir until champagne is absorbed.
Add chicken broth one-half cup at a time, stirring and waiting until liquid is absorbed before adding next 1/2 cup broth.
Cook until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Add lemon peel, cheese and seasonings.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients and place in pie crust.
Cover with second crust and bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: delicious pickled vegetable salad
directions: Combine juice, vinegar, salt and seeds.
Bring to boil; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in vegetables; lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into sterile 1/2 pint jars leaving 3/4-inch at top. Cap with sterile lids and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes after water returns to boiling.
Makes 3 cups.
Two cups contains 28 calories.
One half cup equals one diabetic vegetable exchange.

title: burnt sugar pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup white sugar.
Add 1/2 cup hot water.
Let stand on warm covered until all the sugar and water is dissolved.
Cook until thick.
Remove from stove.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour into baked crust.
Cover with meringue made from 2 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: homemade cheez whiz
directions: Melt together in top of a double boiler or in microwave.
Stir to blend.
Pour into containers.
Makes 3 pints.

title: swiss cheese quiche with ham and spinach
directions: Combine eggs, mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch and pepper; beat with mixer until well blended.
Add cheese, ham and spinach; mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 1 hour, or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Allow quiche to set for 10 minutes before cutting. Garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes, if desired.

title: salsa burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form mixture into 6-8 patties.
Layer patties in aluminum foil and refrigerate until they firm up. broil, gill or bake to desired doneness.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let chill 24 hours before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in sealed container and refrigerate until serving time.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to box.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick like pudding. Let cool down.
Mix together pasta and pudding, then add your fruit cocktail, pineapple, cherries and the Cool Whip.

title: hi-energy candy
directions: Knead, then shape into balls.
Roll in nuts, sesame seed or coconut.

title: tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, carrot, celery and mayonnaise together.
Cut French bread into 4 pieces, and slice each piece lengthwise.
Spread each slice with tuna mixture.
Top with tomato and cheese and bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: chinese ground beef
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper, soup, green beans, sprouts and mushrooms.
Simmer until green beans thaw.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: midwest chili
directions: Add meat, onion and garlic to a heavy Dutch oven.
Break up any lumps with fork and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until meat is browned.
Stir in chile, cumin and salt.
Add the water, tomato sauce and tomatoes, mashing with a fork.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
Stir in beans and simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix well together and let set a few minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Is equal to store bought.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken in water for 20 minutes and debone.
Cook broccoli for less time than on box.
Layer broccoli in large casserole with chicken on top.
Pour soup mixture with rest of ingredients stirred in.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 30 to 35 cupcakes.

title: chocolate raisin rice pudding
directions: Soak rice in milk 30 minutes.
Add salt and cook in double boiler until rice is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix butter, sugar, chocolate, raisins and vanilla.
Add cooked rice, cream and beaten whites.
Fill buttered baking dish; cover with a meringue. Brown in moderate oven at 325° for 30 minutes and serve either hot or cold.

title: chex party mix
directions: You will need 1 gallon zipper bag.

title: logs
directions: Mix all by hand.
Form into logs. Melt 1 cup chocolate chips with 3 tablespoons shortening. Spread on top of logs.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Brown bacon in Dutch oven or large pan with a lid.
Drain bacon; pour off all bacon grease except 2 tablespoons.
Brown onions, peppers and dry rice in bacon grease.
Add peas, undrained.
Add water.
Simmer, covered, until rice is cooked. Add ham and crumbled bacon.
Serve with corn bread.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all together and stir to boiling; use as required.
Unused portion may be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.
Baste chicken as desired or pour over chicken and bake in oven at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Spread your favorite creamy chocolate frosting over cooled brownies and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in buttered dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carolyn's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour dressing over all and mix well.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, orange juice, brown sugar, oil, flour and salt; mix well.
Cook, stirring until mixture comes to a boil and thickens slightly.
Add chicken, pineapple, water chestnuts and ginger.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice and sprinkle with toasted nuts.
Serves 6 to 8.
Double recipe of sauce to make dish a lot juicier.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: In salad bowl combine all ingredients.
Toss well. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight to develop flavor.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and juice from oranges at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn mixer to low speed.
Add oranges.
Mix for 1 minute.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
This can be frozen and will keep a long time.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and slice; boil until tender.
Drain.
Chop onions, pepper and celery.
Combine with carrots and other ingredients.
Chill 24 hours.
Serve cold.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: pinto and meat dish
directions: Cook beans.
Put ground meat and onions in skillet; cook until onions are tender.
Add to rest of dish; cook slowly.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray bottom of 10 x 15-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix coconut and pecans and cover bottom of dish with this mixture.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour
cake mix mixture over pecan mixture.
Then pour cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake in 350°
oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bailey irish crme
directions: Stir by hand or mixer. Put in dark bottles. Let stand for 4 hours.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream shortening, salt, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn and okra creole
directions: Saute pepper and onion 5 minutes. Add corn and okra. Cook on medium heat 8 to 10 minutes. Add tomato paste, tomatoes, thyme, salt, pepper and hot sauce. Mix well; cover. Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: * butter sauce for fish *
directions: Combine and heat.
Pour over baked or fried fish of your choice.

title: proteena puffs
directions: Mash Proteena.
Add the onions and seasoning.
Add enough mayonnaise and cole slaw dressing to make quite moist.
Work the mixture with your hands by squeezing it through your fingers. Keep working it until the pieces are very fine.
Let stand a while.
Can be kept in refrigerator for several days.
Serve as a sandwich spread or in tiny cream puff shells.

title: yogurt
directions: Note:
Need 4 quart jars with lids, 1 large kettle with lid, stainless steel thermometer and heating pad (medium heat).

title: millionaire pie
directions: Pour into graham cracker pie crust; top with whipped cream and chill overnight.

title: shrimp salad deluxe
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water, salted, according to instructions; drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix remaining ingredients and pasta together; toss well.
Refrigerate until well chilled and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried dandelion
directions: Soak the flowers in salt water for 15 minutes.
Rinse well. Coat in cornmeal.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Tastes like fried mushrooms.

title: russian refresher
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons per 8 ounces of hot water.
May add more mix to taste.

title: crawfish touffe at its best
directions: Melt butter in heavy 4 to 5-quart saucepot. Add onions, celery, bell peppers and garlic; cook until soft, about 15 minutes over medium-high heat. Add crawfish, mushrooms, lemon juice and Tabasco. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in flour, mixing well. Add water, green onions and parsley. Bring to a simmer and continue simmering 10 more minutes. Season with salt and pepper and serve over rice. If prepared ahead, reheat gently just until hot.

title: hawaiian carrot torte
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon. In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour mixture a little at a time; mix well after each addition.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut and blend thoroughly.
Turn into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until done.
Cool about 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely and frost between layers and top. Leave sides unfrosted.
Torte with favorite frosting or Cream Cheese Frosting will keep well in the refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: green bean salad
directions: Boil beans and cool. Hard-boil eggs and cool and slice.
Mix together salad dressing, oil, mustard, vinegar, pepper, salt and sugar. Pour over beans and eggs. Mix together.

title: hard candies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, without stirring, to 300° (hard crack stage).
Cool slightly.
Blend in coloring and flavoring.
Pour into greased pan.
While candy is still hot, crease with knife.
Repeat creasing after candy has been allowed to cool a few minutes to a half hour.
Turn pan upside down over board and tap slightly. Break candy carefully along creases.
Yields 1 1/4 pounds.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add pecans.
Put in a loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Cut bread into serving size pieces.
Mix meat, seasonings and pizza sauce.
Spread over bread pieces, covering completely. Broil 6-inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Put slices of cheese on top.
Return to broiler until cheese melts and browns.

title: cowboy smile cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with rotary beater until smooth.
Drizzle batter from teaspoon, forming eyes and mouth.
Bake until brown. Pour 1/2 cup batter over face.
Bake until bubbles appear.
Turn and bake other side until golden brown.

title: baked scallops
directions: Combine scallops, cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup butter, ketchup, salt, pepper and sugar.
Put into shallow casserole pan.
Combine green onions and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Place on top of scallops.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown. Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: lazy days of summer peach cobbler
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sift the next 4 ingredients together.
Cut in the 1/4 cup butter.
Add to flour and butter mixture the milk and beaten egg.
Pour batter over the fruit.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on the batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: stripe-it-rich cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
When cooked, poke holes with a wooden spoon or a straw, about 1 inch.
Then combine pudding mix and sugar in large bowl.
Gradually stir in milk.
Then beat with electric mixer for 1 minute, then pour into holes in cake and let 1/2 of pudding thicken a little; spread on cake like a frosting. Cool 1 hour.
Keep in refrigerator!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in water; set aside and let cool.
Mix sugar with cranberries, then add pineapple with juice, celery and pecans. Add this mixture to the cooled Jell-Os and refrigerate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: With mixer, cream sugar and margarine in mixer bowl until creamy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour 3 times.
Blend soda into sour cream. Add flour and sour cream mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well after each addition. Add flavorings.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into well-greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Add bacon, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over ingredients.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: fruit soup
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Add half pineapple and half orange juice to cover fruit well.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in margarine. Add milk, flour, water and salt; cook into a gravy.
Add soyameat, pimentos and almonds.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Using a 11 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the graham crackers. Mix chocolate pudding using 1/2 large container Cool Whip and 3 cups of the milk and layer over graham crackers.
Add layer of graham crackers.
Mix the vanilla pudding using remaining 1/2 large container Cool Whip and remaining 3 cups milk and layer over graham crackers.
Add layer of graham crackers.
Heat chocolate icing in microwave for 20 seconds or until it will pour.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: 4th of july cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan; let cool.
Cream the cream cheese with 3/4 cup milk; gradually add rest of milk.
Drain pineapple; add to cream cheese mixture.
Spread on cake.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chocoberry splash(beverage)
directions: Fill tall glass with crushed ice.
Into blender container, measure all ingredients except club soda.
Cover; blend on medium speed until smooth.
Pour into glass over ice; add club soda. Serve immediately.
Makes one 12-ounce serving.

title: dad's christmas dates
directions: Split dates on one side and remove the pit.
Insert 1/4 of the whole walnut into the date.
Close the date back up, molding it around the nut.
Roll in powdered sugar or granulated sugar lightly.
Arrange in a pretty little bowl or add to a tray with other Christmas cookies.

title: broccoli casserole #1
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Meanwhile, cook rice according to directions on box.
Combine rice and sauteed vegetables.
Add cheese, soup and thawed broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
French fried onions may be sprinkled over top.

title: yuletime date balls
directions: Mix egg, sugar,
butter or margarine, salt and dates in saucepan and cook,	stirring
frequently
until dates are soft and mixture is	thick.	Place
saucepan
in
iced
water until mixture is cool enough to handle.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts; mix quickly.
Shape into balls with buttered hands; roll balls in coconut.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: spaghetti carbonara(american style)
directions: Saute onion and bacon with oil and butter.
Put a teaspoon of olive oil in boiling water before putting the spaghetti to cook. Set aside in a warm dish when cooked.
Add yolks, parsley, cheese and cream to bacon, stirring over low heat.
Mix cooked spaghetti with egg and cheese mixture; serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: donuts or rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar, salt and lard in hot milk in bowl.
Add water and beaten eggs.
Liquid should be very warm to touch.
Add 4 cups flour; sprinkle dry yeast over it.
Stir with wire whisk.
Add the rest of the flour; stir with big spoon.
Dough should be sticky but manageable.
Makes approximately 50 donuts.

title: western meat-in-one
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add garlic, salt, onion, green pepper and chili powder and saute for 5 minutes or until vegetables are limp. Mix in tomatoes, kidney beans and rice and turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with olives and cheese.
Continue baking for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir in first mixture.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients, mix together.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, water and pepper.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm. Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Keeps up to six weeks.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice meat into 1/2 inch slices; cut slices into 1/2 inch strips.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Brown meat on all sides; remove and reserve.
Saute mushrooms and onion until tender in fat remaining in skillet.
Add meat, beef broth, wine or water, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Recipe may be cooked to this stage and reheated.
Stir in sour cream; heat to just boiling, stirring constantly.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Put 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate, sugar, margarine and egg yolks; cook together for 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites very stiff; fold in chocolate mixture.
Cool for 5 minutes, then smooth over crumbs.
Chill, then spread ice cream over chocolate mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Serves 10 to 12 people.
Delicious!

title: chocolate cake
directions: Make chocolate pudding mix. Add dry cake mix to the hot pudding. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts and chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute several garlic cloves (chopped) in oil.
Add plum tomatoes, basil, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
You can add canned mushrooms, if desired.

title: puffy pineapple pancake
directions: Cut pineapple crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices; set 5 slices aside.
Reserve remaining pineapple for another use.

title: indian tortillas
directions: Mix both flours, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Work in shortening thoroughly.
Add liquid gradually to make a stiff dough. Knead for 5 minutes until springy.
Roll dough into small balls.
Roll balls until round and flat.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Mash cream cheese; add jello with hot water.
Fold in Cool Whip; add pineapple and juice.
Cool until firm.

title: master bread mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 plus cups.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Chop and let drain.
Add all and boil 5 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in accordance with package directions. Drain and combine chicken soup, mayonnaise and eggs. Fold ingredients into broccoli and cover with Ritz cracker crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake in 350° oven about 20-30 minutes.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with milk. Stir in Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate at least one hour to firm.

title: mexican salsa(yields 7 to 8 pints)
directions: Finely chop the first 6 ingredients (I use the food processor).
Combine vegetables in a Dutch oven with mixture of salt, pepper, basil, oregano, seasoned salt and sugar which has been brought to a simmer.
Mix together cornstarch and vinegar. Add to salsa; stir and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pack into hot jars; seal with hot lids.
Process in hot water bath for 15 minutes (open kettle) or in pressure canner 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Combine the Southern Comfort, lemon juice and lemonade concentrate in a pitcher or bowl.
Chill.
Just before serving, transfer the mixture to a punch bowl and add the 7-Up.
If you wish, keep cold with an ice ring colored with red food coloring and dotted with maraschino cherries.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Blend the cream cheese and butter with electric mixer.
Add sugar and vanilla and blend until smooth.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy, add eggs, beat well, sift spices and flour together, add soda to buttermilk, alternate dry ingredients and buttermilk, mix.
Add other ingredients, adding jam last.
Bake 1 hour

title: italian vegetables(low calorie!)
directions: Preparation Time: 10 minutes.
Cooking Time: 25 minutes. Calories: 150.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Set aside tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover rest of ingredients with water, 2 inches above beans.
Add the remaining ingredients 15 minutes before beans are done.

title: vegetable vinaigrette
directions: Mix in saucepan the first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil. Set aside and let cool.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix all other ingredients.
Save enough cheese to put on top.
Combine the mixed ingredients with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: chicken breasts with cheese
directions: Mix chicken soup with wine.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan; place chicken in pan and top each with slice of Swiss cheese.
Spread soup and wine mixture over it.
Sprinkle the 1 cup herb stuffing over top.
Dot with butter.
Cover first half of baking, then uncover.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine in large saucepan sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add milk, syrup and chocolate squares.
Cook on high for 6 minutes after reaching boiling stage.
Remove from heat; add margarine, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish and allow to cool before cutting into squares.
Use larger Pyrex dish if thinner fudge is desired.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix with cream, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper. Turn into buttered casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with remaining butter and sage.
Sprinkle over spinach.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix small amount of milk with sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat well and add remaining milk and other ingredients. Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oil. Add carrot and celery and saute for 2 to 3 minutes. Add broccoli, potato and water. Simmer until vegetables are quite tender. Stir in one cup of milk, and puree the mixture in a blender or food processor. Return to pan and add 1 cup of milk and seasonings. If too liquidy, thicken with 1 Tbsp cornstarch. Mix in 2 Tbsp cold milk and heat. Serves 6.

title: pecan chews
directions: In top of double boiler, melt morsels with Eagle Brand milk. Cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until mixture is thick and smooth. Remove from heat.
In large bowl, mix wheat squares and pecans. Pour morsel mixture over wheat square mixture.
Coat well.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.

title: pineapple mint supreme
directions: Combine flour, nuts, brown sugar and 1/2 cup oleo until fine. Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Bring juice to boiling point.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Blend in jello mixture.
Stir in pineapple. Chill until thick, but not set.
Chill in freezer 2/3 cup Pet milk with 1/8 teaspoon peppermint in bowl until ice crystals form.
Beat until thick.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Spoon over baked crust.
Refrigerate while preparing glaze.
Spoon on filling.
Spread carefully.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix butter and brown sugar together.
Stir in walnuts and Bisquick; mix until crumbly. Reserve 3/4 cup.
Finger press remaining mixture into pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: kugel
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar and cottage cheese.
Use half the sour cream.
Add raisins.
Fold into cooked noodles.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour into pan.
Put spoonfuls of sour cream on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lite spaghetti
directions: Brown turkey in frying pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: wassail
directions: Pour juices into 20-cup electric percolator. Place remaining ingredients in basket. Allow to go through perk cycle. Serve hot. Yield: 20 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy date-nut bars(low-fat - low cholesterol)
directions: Add sugar and oil to eggs; blend well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients, then add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Pour into greased or sprayed 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan and then cut into bars.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, then
drain off grease real good.
Put back in pan and put
taco seasoning and water in.
Let simmer, then add remaining ingredients.

title: cinnamon pecan ring
directions: Grease a 12-inch pizza pan; set aside.
On a lightly floured surface, flatten thawed dough slightly.
Cut each loaf into 4 pieces (8 pieces total).
Form each piece into a rope, about 18-inches long.
Brush each rope on all sides with melted margarine or butter.
Mix together brown and granulated sugars and cinnamon.
Place in shallow pan or on large sheet of foil.
Roll rope in mixture (keep hooking together).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans on top and all remaining sugar.
Cover and let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Or cover with plastic wrap and let rise overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir together powdered sugar, milk and vanilla for glaze.
Spoon over top and add pecan halves.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Add nuts.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Mix pudding milk and lemon extract; spread on last layer.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: chicken dip - very good
directions: Soften cheese and mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk and well beaten eggs. Stir over medium heat until thick. Pour in pie shell.

title: keep it barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add other ingredients.
Heat and serve.
May be kept in refrigerator indefinitely.
Best on ham or pork.

title: crispy baked veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
In bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Place flour in a separate bowl.
Whisk egg and water in a third bowl.
Dip veggies in flour, then egg, then bread crumbs.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Drizzle with oil.
Bake 22 to 24 minutes total; turn after 12 minutes.
Need to be tender and lightly bronze.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a serving dish or a fondue dish.
Keep warm when serving.
Accompany with chunks of French bread, breadsticks or crackers.

title: chicken fil gumbo
directions: Put cooking oil in heavy pot. Heat up, then add the flour. Brown flour and oil together until brown (the color your want the gumbo), then add the onions. Cook until tender, then add your bell peppers. Add your chicken and cook about 10 to 15 minutes. Fill pot with water and add the rest of our seasoning to the pot. Add the sausage if you wanted at this time. When gumbo is cooked and the sauce is like you want it, add the fil. Serve with hot rice and potato salad.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Form into pancake-sized patties. Fry on both sides until golden brown.

title: creole meatballs
directions: Make meatballs and place in casserole dish.

title: savory chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Brown in hot butter.
Combine cornstarch and vinegar and cook with sugar until clear.
Add Tabasco, Worcestershire, mustard and red and green peppers.
Cut in large pieces.
Add pineapple and juice. Pour over chicken in casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Pour boiling water over corn meal.
Stir to keep from lumping until cooled slightly.
Add butter and egg yolks and stir until eggs are thoroughly blended.
Stir in buttermilk.
Blend in sugar and soda. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: acorn squash wedges
directions: Halve squash through stem end.
Scrape out seeds and fiber. Halve each piece through stem end.
Arrange, cut side up, in baking dish.

title: bowwow bean bake
directions: Cook onion in hot fat until tender but not brown.
Slice two of the frankfurters in rounds, then combine with beans, molasses, mustard and salt.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of the bean and frankfurter mixture with tomatoes and onion. Arrange the remaining frankfurters in spoke fashion on top.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: flour tortillas
directions: You will also need foil laminated paper baking cups.

title: glazed persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pudding ingredients.
Pour onto a large cookie sheet (about 11 x 17-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown around edges.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Combine Hidden Valley Ranch, oil, garlic salt and dill weed and make up ahead of time (best if made up the night before). Keep in refrigerator before use.
Pour mixture on crackers and mix well.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Pour flour in bowl; mix sugar, butter and brown sugar, then mix vanilla in with everything.
Take a teaspoon of dough and roll a little ball.
Place flat on the cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° until lightly browned.

title: bow tie casserole
directions: Dice onions.
Heat oil and add onions; heat thoroughly.
Add meat and sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Cook bow ties; drain.
Add to meat and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: lo-cal fruit milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until light and fluffy.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine in large mixing bowl in microwave for one minute.
Add sugar and milk, stirring to mix.
Microwave on High 3 minutes; stir, then 2 minutes and mix well.
Scrape bowl. Microwave on High 3 minutes; stir, then 2 1/2 minutes.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Do not stir until ingredients are all together.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick dessert
directions: Sift dry jello into cottage cheese and mix.
Add small can mandarin oranges, drained.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Lemon or lime jello and crushed pineapple drained may be substituted.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken in 3-quarts water until done.
Reserve stock. Cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
In large skillet, heat oil and stir in flour.
Cook until dark brown.
Add onions and celery. Simmer until onions are clear.
Add ham or sausage, tomatoes and 1/3 chicken stock.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cubed chicken and remaining stock, garlic and bay leaf.
Cook 1 1/4 hours on low. Stir occasionally.
Drain thawed okra and add; cook 45 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix with salad dressing.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Mash 1 boiled egg.
Top with bacon bits.
Chill and serve.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Heat sugar in small, heavy saucepan over medium low heat, stirring constantly until dissolved and caramel colored.
Quickly pour into bottom of deep dish 9 inch pie plate; swirl around bottom and sides to coat.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt the butter in a large pot.
Add the onion, carrots and celery; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring from time to time. Add the potatoes and parsley; stir until coated.
Stir in the stock; cook, partially uncovered, until the potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Put through a strainer, or puree in a blender or food processor.
Return to the pot.
Stir in the cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Reheat without boiling.
Serve hot or cold.

title: no knead feather rolls
directions: Mix and brush top with melted butter and let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down and spoon into buttered muffin tins.
Let rise until dough reaches almost top of pans.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ranch dip
directions: Melt velveeta cheese. Then add sour cream and ranch dressing. Heat for 1 minute.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream shortening; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: holiday carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each egg.
Sift flour, soda powder, salt and cinnamon; add to oil and sugar mixture.
Mix well and add the carrots and pecans.
Mix well. Pour into three greased cake pans and bake at 350° until done. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine herbs spices from spaghetti mix.
Mix well with oil solution.
Mix vegetables together.
Prepare spaghetti as directed on package except break into thirds.
Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a jar or decanter. Use 2 rounded teaspoonfuls in a cup of boiling water.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Simmer all ingredients in saucepan.
Pour over cleaned chicken and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: dolly bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour milk over evenly.
Top with remaining ingredients; press gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off of peppers and clean out seeds.
Arrange peppers in a large saucepan.
Mix hamburger, rice, egg, milk, onion and salt together and use mixture to stuff peppers.
Mix soup and water together and pour over peppers.
Cook over medium heat about 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix together the Eagle Brand and lemon juice. Stir until thick. Drain the fruit cocktail or oranges; stir into Cool Whip. Fold fruit and Cool Whip into milk mixture. Slice cake into 3 equal layers.
Spread mixture like frosting between layers, on the sides and pour any that's left into center of cake.
Refrigerate before and after serving.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put oysters in layers in baking dish, alternating with crumbs, bits of butter and salt and pepper to taste.
When dish is full, add oyster liquor and milk to moisten. Cover with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serves six.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Combine flour and nuts to creamed mixture, mixing just until smooth. Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour or until done.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover the beef stew meat in water in a large pot.
Cook the meat in the water for 15 to 20 minutes. Add soups, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes that have been cubed and sliced carrots. Cook on low simmer until all are tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; serve chilled.

title: potato chowder
directions: Boil potatoes; set water aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion to bacon grease; saute 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Add potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and sour cream gradually.
Add milk slowly, then seasonings.
Do not boil.
(This only fills crock-pot to 1/2 to 2/3.
If you are feeding very many, double recipe.)

title: banana super shake
directions: In blender container, combine bananas, lemon juice, water and milk.
Blend well.
Add ice, blending until smooth.
Serve in frosted glasses.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 5 cups.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cut sausages into small slices.
Layer croutons, sausages and cheese.
Should make 2 layers in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard until foamy.
Pour evenly over croutons, cheese and sausages.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes; if glass pan is used, 45 minutes.
Great for brunch. Make the night before and bake in the morning.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: mountain high icing
directions: In a small saucepan, mix flour and milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until a smooth paste is made.
Set aside until lukewarm.

title: broiled trout
directions: Place fillets in greased casserole.
Sprinkle onion and tomatoes over fillets.
Broil 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and broil another 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. ball's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into baking dish and cook at 400° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well. Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add raisins, pineapple and nuts and mix.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or mix will fit in 2 greased and floured bread pans and bake for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Rinse and drain artichokes.
Either mash or chop in food processor.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Preheat oven to 300° and bake in baking dish for 20 minutes or until slightly brown and bubbly.

title: apache cheese bread
directions: Cut top of bread off and scoop out inside. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Fill bread with mixture. Replace the top. Wrap in foil and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 1 hour. Serve with chips and rest of bread.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix raisins, cherries and nuts with crackers. Melt over low heat the marshmallows with the cream.
Pour over mixture; blend well.
Press in wax paper lined cracker box and refrigerate.

title: farmer chow
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain fat.
Add beef to bacon and brown.
Add vegetables and cook until veggies are soft.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° at least 1 hour.
Can freeze half for later use.

title: easter eggs
directions: Soften
butter
and cream cheese and mix together, then add remaining
ingredients.
Place
in refrigerator to chill. Shape into eggs and put into refrigerator to harden.
Dip eggs in melted chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: santa's fruit cake
directions: Sprinkle dates, pineapple, nuts and cherries with 1/4 cup flour.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Sift 1 1/4 cups flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to sugar mixture. Fold in fruit and pack in well-greased and paper-lined tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a large, heavy skillet.
Add consomme, wine (or cranberry cocktail), soy sauce, garlic and onion powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour, or until meat is tender.

title: creole meat balls for spaghetti
directions: Add egg and bread crumbs to meat; mix.
Add all seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls with hands.
Fry until brown in olive oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean mushrooms; remove caps and chop stems.
Mix cracker crumbs with spices, onions and melted butter. Add chopped mushroom stems.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place 2/3 cup butter in large saucepan; add celery and saute until tender.
(Do not brown.)
Combine cubed bread, onion flakes, parsley, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Add celery; toss to mix.
Set aside.
In same saucepan, melt 1 cup butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in chicken soup mix, water, milk and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add some hot mixture to eggs; blend well. Pour back into hot mixture; cook 1 minute.
Stir sauce and chicken into celery bread mixture.
Turn into greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Toss bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Makes 12 servings.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken; top with Swiss cheese. Pour dressing over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: grandma birdi's bread pudding
directions: Cut crusts off bread; save for crumbs.
Cover bread with milk to soften.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Butter baking dish; sprinkle with crust crumbs.
Pour all ingredients in pan.
Top with more crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: traditional cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients. Mix well.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until onions are lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in jar. When ready to serve, add 2 teaspoons mixture to 1 cup water.

title: crisp sweet pickles(quick)
directions: Put the
celery
seed, salt and cloves in a bag.
Slice medium size cucumbers in about 1/4-inch slices.
Cover with a mixture of 2 cups lime and 2 gallons of water.
Let stand for 24
hours, stirring
occasionally.
Rinse
cucumbers well and soak for 3 hours in clear, cold water, then drain well.
Bring to a
boil the vinegar, sugar and spices;
let cool a little, then
pour over the drained cucumbers and let stand overnight. Next morning,
boil all
for
40 minutes.
(I let them simmer after they
come to a boil.) Pack pickles into sterilized jars and pour hot liquid over them and seal.
Yields 7 or 8 pints.

title: chicken loaf with sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan and sprinkle with some bread crumbs.
Toast 12 slices of dry white bread until dry and golden brown.
Roll with rolling pin to make crumbs.

title: oven-cooked beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch cubes, sprinkle with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Melt 3 tablespoons oil in skillet and brown meat well.
Transfer meat to a 2-quart casserole.
Lightly brown onion in fat and add to meat.
Add seasoning and celery and stir well. Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add can of peas, vegetables and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir into meat. Cover and continue baking for 20 minutes or until cooked.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine ham with parsley, green pepper, eggs, cheese, onion and lemon juice.
Cover broccoli with ham mixture.
Top with cream sauce.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: deep dish chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked deep dish pie shell or 2 regular pie shells.
Top with meringue and bake in 375° oven about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: Brush a large piece of heavy aluminum foil with butter.
In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch thick wedges.
Place in foil and brush oil mixture on potatoes.
Tightly seal edges of foil.
Place on grill.
Cook 1 hour.

title: tomato and red onion salad with goat cheese
directions: Layer tomato slices attractively on plate.
Top with onion and cheese.
Mix together vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper and olive oil.
Pour over salad.
Garnish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil; add beaten eggs and water.
Add spices and flour; mix thoroughly.
Place in 2 large or 3 medium loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
After removing from oven, brush with melted butter.
Freezes well.
Enjoy!

title: cheese and beef quiche
directions: Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix; shape into a loaf.
Put into a nonstick bread pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn critters
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add with milk to eggs. Add corn and drop by tablespoons into hot oil until browned.

title: pumpkin apple strussel muffins
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press into top of muffins.

title: soft chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Sift into mixture flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: breakfast chunkies
directions: Stir the flour, oatmeal, sesame seed, wheat germ, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl until blended.
Add the peanuts, walnuts, raisins, dates and sunflower seeds; stir to coat.
Beat the oil, maple syrup, egg and banana together.
Fold into the dry ingredients until blended.
Drop by rounded 1/4 cupfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake until bottoms are golden, 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 20 cookies.

title: fresh pineapple dip
directions: Mix juice, egg, flour and sugar together.
Heat to boil and thicken.
Cool.
Fold into whipped cream.
Keep cold.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hot turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together into a casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 11-inch quiche pan, 10-inch pie pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
(If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.)
Cut into wedges to serve. Serves 6.

title: grade a venison roast
directions: You will also need a large roasting bag.

title: ham deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks.
Add mayonnaise, cream cheese, mustard and lemon juice, stirring until smooth.
Stir in ham, dill weed and salt.
Spoon or pipe into egg white halves.

title: yankee cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Blend in oats and swiftly stir in milk and egg.
Blend 1/3 cup brown sugar with 2 tablespoons soft butter. Pat into greased muffin pans. Arrange pecan halves in pan and pour mixture over. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: apple-cream coffee cake
directions: In small bowl, mix nuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream butter and 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy with beater at full speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda, beating well.
Add cream.
Spread half of batter in pan; top with apples.
Top apples with nut mixture.
Add remaining batter.
Add remaining nut mixture.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for tossed salad.
Drain and rinse beans. Add diced tomatoes, diced onions, cheese and beans to lettuce. Chill.
Just before serving, toss with Fritos and Catalina dressing.
Goes well with King Ranch Chicken.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix together into crumb mixture.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Drain sauce from pork and beans.
Put beans, brown sugar, ketchup, onion and bacon bits in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until thick.
Serve hot or warm.

title: turkey pasta sauce
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in olive oil in a large pot on medium-high heat for about 10 minutes.
Add turkey sausage and turkey and crumble; cook at medium heat, crumbling turkey and stirring until turkey loses pink color.
If using wine, add wine and cook at medium-high heat until most of wine liquid has evaporated.
Add the tomatoes (chop some of the tomatoes in the pot with a spatula, if whole) and lower heat to keep simmering.
Simmer one or two hours.
Serve over your favorite pasta.
More than enough sauce for one pound of pasta.

title: tempera batter
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir (do not beat).
Batter should be lumpy.
For a thicken batter, use less water.
Also good with Tony's Creole seasoning.
Delicious for shrimp, vegetables, etc.

title: dress me up salad
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and pecans together and add to all other ingredients. You may add more sour cream for moisture. Place in serving bowl and chill.

title: stuff lettuce
directions: Hollow out heart of lettuce, leaving about 1-inch shell of leaves.
Blend together Bleu cheese and mayonnaise.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on the box.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Just mix, roll out and cut with a cutter.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes medium-size biscuits.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup milk.
Scald 1 1/2 cups milk, stir into gelatine to dissolve.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Set aside. Beat eggs at high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Add the two milks, pudding mix and vanilla.
Then add gelatine mixture.
Takes 20 minutes to freeze.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Slice vegetables.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed. Heat until sugar is melted.
Pour mixture over vegetables. Marinate overnight or 1 to 2 days.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut crust away from bread.
Spread with butter and place in a greased casserole dish.
Brown sausage, stirring to crumble. Drain well.
Sprinkle over top of bread.
Sprinkle cheese over top of sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add half and half and salt to eggs.
Pour over top of cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Let it sit out of refrigerator for 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach cakes(a caribbean recipe)
directions: Wash spinach leaves after removing stems and chop finely.
Beat egg in a mixing bowl.
Add onion, melted margarine and spinach. Sift in flour, bread crumbs, salt and baking powder; blend well. Add some milk to make mixture just firm enough to drop from a spoon.
Heat oil in a deep fryer or a suitable skillet.
Drop mixture in hot fat by the spoonful and cook until golden.

title: corn bread dressing with chicken and rice soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo; pour onion and celery mixture over crumbled corn bread.
Add poultry seasoning and garlic, then add undiluted chicken and rice soup; mix well and add egg.
Bake at 400° until edges are brown.
Bake pieces of broiler chicken on top, if desired.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks, lemon juice and grated lemon rind well. Pour into crust.
Beat rest of ingredients (butter and egg whites) until foam peak.
Add sugar until stiff and bake until golden brown.

title: black cherry delight
directions: Mix together and pour on chilled graham cracker crust.
Top with 1 large can black pie cherries (drained).
Chill.

title: special chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Mix cornstarch with chicken stock and stir in onion and pepper.
Add soy sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken. Pour over 2 cups cooked rice.
Top with tomato wedges.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion and celery 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until broccoli breaks apart and well mixed.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Mix cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Let stand overnight. Next day, mix well.
Let stand overnight again.
In mixer, mix remainder of ingredients.
Serves 12.

title: rolled fillet of sole
directions: Wipe each fillet and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese and onion on each fillet.
Roll jelly-roll style and secure with toothpick.
Dip each rolled fillet in egg or water wash.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Place in well buttered dish.
Pour melted butter over top and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place under broiler until bread crumbs brown, 1 or 2 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
Even if you are not a seafood cook, try this.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Blend in eggs.
Gradually add melted
margarine to dry ingredients.
Continue mixing while gradually adding flour and then vanilla.

title: candied carrots
directions: Put all ingredients in saute pan.
Cook on medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: new orleans shrimp
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter in large skillet until almost tender.
Stir in bay leaf, salt, thyme, basil and cayenne pepper.
Chop tomatoes.
Add to skillet. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce and okra.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf; add shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink.
Cook noodles using package directions. Drain.
Serve sauce over noodles.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Crumble margarine, brown sugar and pecans over top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Pour melted butter over corn flakes.
Add mayonnaise and other seasonings.
Mix in crab meat with fork so it will not pack.
Fill crab backs or individual containers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cream pie
directions: Stir and heat to thicken.
Pour into baked shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Cook mixture slowly (approximately 2 hours) on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hamburger buns.
Serves approximately 8.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 1/2 cup boiling water; add flour and salt and stir vigorously, cooking until mixture forms a stiff ball. Remove from heat.
Make well in middle of ball and break eggs into well.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Drop dough onto lightly greased baking sheet in teaspoonfuls (about 24).
Bake 10 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Remove, cool and split.

title: tater tot hamburg casserole
directions: Brown
hamburg
with
onion, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole.
Add
corn
and mix lightly.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Dilute
cream
of mushroom soup with milk; pour over top of Tater Tots.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: alabama pie
directions: In oblong cake pan, spread pie filling, next pineapple and sprinkle coconut over this.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over this. Cut up margarine in small slices over top and add nuts to top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potted shrimp(recipe from the vikings' restaurant in bangkok)
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion and garlic in the olive oil just until they begin to soften. Stir in the shrimp, rosemary, paprika, salt and pepper to taste and white wine.
Cook the mixture for a few minutes. Stir in the tomato sauce and the parsley. Cook the mixture for about 5 minutes more or until shrimp are done.
Add the cheese and stir it until it is almost melted. Divide the mixture among 4 earthenware pots and top each serving with a spoonful of sour cream and some finely chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp mold
directions: In microwave or top of double boiler, combine soup, gelatin and cream cheese.
Heat until melted.
Remove and add mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into mold.

title: edith's posh squash
directions: Cook squash until tender in salted water.
Drain squash well. Mix
with
other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in buttered dish 30 to 40 minutes.
May use bread crumbs on top.

title: granola
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
In a saucepan, heat remaining ingredients, except raisins.
Add the hot mixture to the ingredients in the bowl.
Spread this mixture on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 to 50 minutes. Stir mixture every 15 minutes.
Stir raisins into baked mixture. Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts granola.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave on high for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Add soda, stir till foamy. Pour into buttered salted cookie sheet and spread.
Cool and break up.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese soften, then mix everything together until well blended.
Roll into large or small balls.
Roll into finely chopped nuts.

title: funnel cake
directions: Use an electric skillet with 1/2 full of oil.
When oil gets hot take mixture of first 5 ingredients (mixed well), pour mixture (1/2 cup) through funnel.
Move into a circular motion and then crisscross motion.
Turn when it becomes brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into a pastry lined pie plate.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer or until pie is set and crust is browned.

title: butternut squash bake
directions: Add margarine to mashed squash.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 2-quart dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together the brown sugar, margarine, syrup, flour, water and eggs.
Gradually add cake mix to mixture.
When mixed, add raisins or dates and walnuts.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until brown.
When cool, cut in pieces.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar substitute.
Beat in eggs, water and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl. Add dry mix to creamed mixture, stirring to blend thoroughly. Stir in chocolate mini-chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. This cookie will not brown as other chocolate chip cookies.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine in a 2-quart saucepan the margarine, cocoa and water. Heat to boiling.
Remove and add flour, salt, soda and sugar. Beat until mixed.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream and eggs; blend.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes in a greased pan (15 x 11 1/2-inch).

title: creamy lemon cheese cake
directions: Measure 1 cup cake mix; set aside.
Combine remaining mix with 1 egg and oil.
Press in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: low-fat italian salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill overnight.
This salad keeps well for several days.

title: sausage skillet scramble
directions: Saute sausage, onions and apples in oil in a large skillet until onions and apple slices are tender, stirring constantly. Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Spoon over fresh fruit (cut in bite size).
Mix gently.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Beat egg until lemon colored.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Dip a few onion rings at a time into the batter so that each ring is completely covered.
Drop the rings, a few at a time, into hot shortening.

title: jerk ribs
directions: In a small jar with a tight-fitting lid, shake together all dry ingredients until well blended.
Rub dry mixture onto all surfaces of ribs.
Grill ribs over indirect heat in covered grill, turning occasionally, until ribs are very tender, about 1 1/2 hours (or roast ribs on rack in shallow pan in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours).
Cut into 1 or 2-rib portions to serve.
Serves 10. Preparation Time:
10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
90 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Combine remaining cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg. Press into pan.
Combine pumpkin pie mix, 2 eggs and 2/3 cup milk. Pour over crust.
Combine 1 cup reserved cake mix, cinnamon, sugar and 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve with whipped topping.
Keep refrigerated.

title: potato salad
directions: Toss ingredients to mix.
Garnish with parsley and paprika. Let stand in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Yields 5 servings, 1 cup each.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle. Place in 9-inch pie plate.
Turn under edge; flute.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and thickened.
Cool; spread onto bottom of pastry shell.

title: mexican pick-up sticks
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Drizzle with melted butter. Stir to combine. Sprinkle with seasoning mix and stir. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Saute green onion, celery, green pepper and slivered almonds. Add ground ginger, soy sauce and pepper.
Mix water and cornstarch; add to vegetable mix and cook until thick.
Add chicken, pineapple and chestnuts; simmer 10 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternating with milk, but ending with flour mixture.
Fold in 2 cups blueberries (which have been floured from part of 2 cups).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon, mixed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Mix water and all ingredients except 1/4 cup of barbecue sauce. Shape meat mixture into oval loaf in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, top with remaining 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center is no longer pink.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in a heavy large skillet. Add tomatoes and juice. Stir in rice, spices and seasoning. Cover with tight-fitting lid. Let cook about 20 to 25 minutes on medium to low heat until rice is cooked, stirring occasionally. Serve with cottage cheese and salad. Keeps in refrigerator up to a week.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add thawed strawberries.
Blend together bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Blend all together and pour into an oblong dish and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Break up angel food cake into bite size pieces and mix with Cool Whip mixture. Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix capped strawberries with glaze and put on top of cake mixture.
Refrigerate.
(Can substitute nonfat sour cream and lite Cool Whip.)

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine crab meat, bread crumbs, scallions, milk, mayonnaise, parsley, salt and pepper.
With moistened hands, form into 8 small round cakes.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour. Place flour on a sheet of wax paper.
Lightly coat each cake on both sides.

title: tuna macaroni
