directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Pour into baking dish and blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Add kidney, lima and pork and beans. Boil the brown sugar, vinegar and mustard; pour over beans and meat. You can cook on the stove top or bake in the oven. If baked, bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage rolls(holupky)
directions: Core and wash head of cabbage, place in a large kettle and cover with water.
Put a lid on and boil until cabbage is wilted. Cook rice until tender and absorbed all water.
Drain and cool head of cabbage.
Combine meat and cooked rice.
Cut stiff vein from cabbage leaf and place a small amount of meat mixture in center.
Fold over and roll leaf up.
Place in roaster and cover with tomato soup and cover with lid.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. May serve with mashed
potatoes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Crush crackers and put in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order given and mix well.
Spray Teflon Bundt pan with Mazola spray or grease and flour non-Teflon
Bundt pan.
Dump mix into pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuit
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Mix butter and garlic powder and brush aver warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Makes 10 - 12 biscuits.

title: braised lemon pork chops
directions: Slowly brown pork chops in frying pan on both sides.
Pour off drippings and salt.

title: pennsylvania dutch vegetable skillet
directions: In large skillet, layer cabbage, carrots, broccoli, pepper slices and ham cubes.
Pour water over and cover.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Drain pineapple, saving 3/4 cup juice.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and cornstarch, mixing thoroughly. Stir in the reserved pineapple juice.
Cut 6 slices pineapple in half and add with juice mixture to skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Serve immediately over rice or chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Stir in Hellmann's and gelatine.
Stir in celery, onions and shrimp. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: yummy rhubarb bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and butter.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and rhubarb.
Mix well.
Pour over baked crust and return to oven (350°) for an additional 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix Well. Drink 2 oz a day.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
In a bowl, mix cottage cheese with strawberry jello. Add in the drained fruit, then fold in the Cool Whip and pecans. Chill until hardens.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix and cheese.
Add milk and eggs, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve warm.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Steam broccoli with 1/2 stick oleo until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Add 1/2 stick oleo.
Add celery, onions, bell pepper and garlic; cook until tender.
Add rice and mushroom soup.
Layer in casserole dish.
Layer rice and beef mixture first, broccoli, French fried onions and cheese.
Top with French fried onions and cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is melted, about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs; beat well.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt that has been sifted together.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cake is baked, spread on topping and put under broiler for about 2 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble half the cornbread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chop vegetables and put on cornbread. Sprinkle bacon on top.
Mix mayo, sugar and pickles.
Pour over bacon.
Top with remaining 1/2 of the cornbread crumbs.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Grease 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, onion, milk and 2 eggs; beat 20 strokes.
Spread in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon over top.
Heat oven to 375° and bake until set, about 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting 6 to 8 servings.

title: mixed rice salad
directions: In 2 to 3-quart pan, bring water to boil.
Add rice and return to boil.
(Do not use seasoning packet.)
Cover pan and cook on low heat until water is absorbed and rice is tender (about 30 minutes).
Uncover and let rice cool to room temperature, about 30 minutes.

title: diabetic prune bread
directions: Mix prunes, raisins, vanilla, soda and boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix flour, nuts and Equal.
When the prune mixture is cold, mix in flour mixture.
Dough will be real stiff, but don't add any more moisture.
Spray two loaf pans with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ground beef along bottom of dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place onion on this.
Arrange Tater Tots over this. Pour undiluted soup over beef and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle grated cheese over casserole and allow to melt.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch and gradually add water.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute; add fruit.
Pour in 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 inch baking dish.

title: cheese nut bread
directions: Combine the dry ingredients and wet ingredients in separate bowls; combine wet to dry.
Stir in nuts and cheese and pour into greased baking pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, walnuts and flour.
Stir in margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture into 8-inch square pan and bake at 350 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes, remove. While crust is baking, beat cream cheese and white sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add lemon juice, milk and vanilla.
Blend.
Pour onto baked crust and top with the reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Enjoy!

title: fettuccine alle pietro
directions: Melt 1/2 the butter in a heavy skillet and brown pork well. Add sauce and simmer, covered, 25 minutes.
Melt remaining butter separately and saute peas and mushrooms for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add peas and mushrooms to pork sauce.
Keep warm over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Serve fettuccine on a platter and pour over the pork tomato sauce.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Preheat grill for 6 minutes.
Combine beef, cheese and oregano.
Mix well.
Shape into two or four 3 1/2 inch patties. Place patties on grill, close lid and cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Serve on English muffins.
Top with pizza sauce if desired.
Makes 2 or 4 servings.

title: diabetic stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large frypan.
In bag, combine flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Shake meat in bag, then brown meat in heated skillet.
Sprinkle remaining flour from bag into the fat very slowly and stir.
Add water and Worcestershire. Pour meat in pan and cover.
Cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables and dill and cook 1 hour more.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Butter a large, covered casserole.
Put rice in the bottom (these are all juicy vegetables; the rice is to absorb juice). Cut squash or zucchini into pieces.
Add chopped celery.
Cut other vegetables into good size pieces and arrange on top of squash.
Sprinkle with basil and brown sugar; dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once after an hour.

title: vegetable sauces
directions: Blend butter and flour thoroughly; add liquid gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat, stirring.
Add seasonings.
Cover tightly and place over hot water until ready to use.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice lengthwise, remove seeds and slice as many cucumbers as necessary.
Slice onions, same fashion.
Lightly salt veggies and refrigerate overnight.
(Salt draws water from veggies.)
Drain veggies; pat dry.
Add sour cream dressing and seasonings.

title: string beans and beef
directions: Prepare marinade of soy sauce, sugar, cornstarch, salt and sherry.
Marinate meat.
Heat pan.
Add 3 tablespoons of oil and saute beef a few seconds.
Prepare beans as indicated on package. Add beans to meat with water they were cooked in.
Simmer a few seconds.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy chicken chowderwoodland park, colorado
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan, cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Cook zucchini, carrots and onion until tender (5 minutes). Drain and set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cover and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Add carrots, celery, basil and parsley.
Season well.
Mix and cook 6 minutes.
Partly cover over medium heat.

title: crescent puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place 1/3 cup filling inside crescent rolls.
(Keep 2 crescent
rolls together to form a square, pressing perforations to seal tightly.) Bring ends together and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Can put seasoned bread crumbs on outside of pastry.

title: griddle cakes
directions: *May use whites of 2 eggs only, not using yolks.

title: "novelty" popcorn cake
directions: After you pop popcorn, set aside in big bowl.
Melt marshmallows with the 1 stick oleo.
Pour over popcorn; add the peanuts and M&M's.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan very well.
Press mixture into pan.
Allow to set overnight.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put crust on top.
Rub milk or cream on top of crust; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Mix the yogurt and Cool Whip together well.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze.
Set out 5 minutes before serving.

title: maryland crab soup
directions: Mix soup with milk.
Heat on medium heat, stirring constantly until lumps are gone.
Add butter, crab and Old Bay, stirring constantly.
Makes 3 to 4 small servings.
Can be doubled.

title: crystal-cut candy
directions: Combine to boiling. Cook to hard crack stage (290°).
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch metal pan.

title: pastry puffs
directions: Add shortening and salt to boiling water and heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Add flour, all at once, and stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball around spoon, leaving pan clean.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating very thoroughly, after each addition.
Continue beating until mixture is thick and shiny.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in bottom of pan.
Mix milk, sugar and flour and pour over butter.
Pour peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and pumpkin.
Add to this mixture flour, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a jelly roll pan.
Pour mixture into pan; spread evenly.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes.
Run spatula under it to make sure it is not stuck.
Turn out onto smooth towel while hot.
Roll up in towel.
Let cool completely.

title: chocolate  midnight madness
directions: In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat in chocolate and vanilla until smooth. Pour into pie crust; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Chill 4 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil and orange juice.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 batter.
Place apple mixture over batter.
Pour rest of batter over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper.
Skin and debone chicken. Put in greased pan and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked peach halves
directions: Bring butter, cinnamon stick, syrup and brown sugar to a boil. Place peach halves in buttered baking pan, putting a maraschino cherry in center of each.
Pour syrup mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Wash and remove large outer leaves around artichokes. Cut off stems with scissors and trim points 1 1/2-inches down from the top. Spread leaves apart. Combine crumbs, garlic, anchovies, parsley, cheese, salt, pepper and oil and mix thoroughly. Place crumbs mixture between loosened artichoke leaves. Stand straight up in saucepan and pour water into pan from side. Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes. Leaves should pull off easily. Remove artichokes very carefully. Serve hot or cold.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased bread pans (2) or 3 small bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake
directions: Brown top and bottom of chops in lightly greased skillet. Sprinkle with salt and set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions. Spoon mixture into 9 x 13 baking dish. Arrange pork chops over potatoes. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Serve.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix ground beef, 1/4 cup water, milk, egg, picante sauce and grated cheese.
Form meatballs and brown in margarine.
Add chopped vegetables and beef broth.
Simmer until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: ice cream dream punch
directions: Put ice cream and sherbet in a large bowl; let soften. Mix with large spoon. Add pineapple juice and Hawaiian Punch drink.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pistachio coconut squares
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix. Add coconut and pineapple and stir. Spoon into 8 x 4 or 9 x 5 inch loaf pan and freeze 3 hours. To serve, dip pan in warm water to unmold.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly; add remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbling.
Pour into baking dish, put pastry on top and cook in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until crust is brown.

title: party chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Wrap bacon around halved breasts; arrange over beef.
Saute mushrooms in butter and spread over chicken.
Combine soup, sherry and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray nonstick cooking oil on 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place 1 pack crescent rolls on dish.
Pat down.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Pour over crescent rolls. Place second pack of crescent rolls on top.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top. Bake 25 minutes.

title: the cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix together by hand.
When well blended, pour into large greased tube (angel) pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cereal, pretzels and nuts.
Set aside.
In a microwave safe bowl, heat the chips at 70% power for 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave 30-45 seconds longer or until chips are melted.
Stir until smooth.
Immediately pour over the cereal mixture and toss to coat evenly.
Spread on waxed paper lined baking sheets to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop chicken, bell pepper, onion and mushrooms coarsely. Saute in oil until chicken is done.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly and serve over cooked spaghetti.
Can be put in casserole, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese and baked.

title: festive sherbet terrine
directions: Line a 6-cup loaf pan with plastic wrap, letting sides and ends extend above pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup cookie crumbs over bottom. Spoon on 2 cups sherbet; press with back of spoon into an even layer.
Repeat layers twice, using remaining cookie crumbs and sherbet.
Fold plastic wrap tightly over top.
Freeze for at least 6 hours or overnight.
Unfold plastic wrap on top.
Invert Terrine on serving plate and remove plastic.
Garnish with raspberries and kiwi fruit just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: spicy pumpkin muffins
directions: Line microwave-safe muffin cups or 6 (6 ounce) glass custard cups with 2 paper baking cups.
Mix flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Beat butter and sugar in medium size bowl with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, pumpkin, milk and honey.
Beat on high speed 2 to 3 minutes until pale (mixture looks slightly curdled).
Stir in flour mixture, then nuts.
Scoop about 3 tablespoons batter into each cup.
Arrange custard cups in a circle in oven.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium-high 4 to 5 minutes, rearranging cups or rotating pan 1/2 turn once, until top springs back when gently pressed.
(Moist spots on top will dry on standing.)
Discard outer paper liners.
Cool on wire racks. Repeat or cover batter and refrigerate up to 3 days.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and salad mix until well blended.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
tags: Hidden Valley Italian salad dressing mix

title: caribbean pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a shallow dish.
Make a marinade of other ingredients.
Pour the marinade over the meat.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Remove meat from marinade. Heat marinade.
Grill or broil as desired, basting frequently with hot marinade.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Cook chicken in butter.
Drain. Then stir in soup, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low. Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and broccoli is done, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Mix in order given; pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle on top 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trawler's famous crab dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip and drained pineapple. Sprinkle jello over the mixture.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until set.
Good for light eaters and gatherings.

title: fabulous pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edge.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add butter, egg yolks and buttermilk until all is well mixed.
Fold in egg whites last. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife test comes out clean.

title: ham spread
directions: Combine ham and cheese in food processor or blender.
Add mustard, brown sugar and cloves.
Process until combined well. Put in crock and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: copper carrots
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Mix well.
Add carrots, onion and green pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for 12 hours.

title: *frozen pumpkin parfait squares
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter; press into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Fold into softened ice cream.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Top with whipped cream or nondairy whipped topping and pecans.
Makes 9 (3-inch) squares.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on high until real hot. Serve hot with chips.

title: mrs. black's icing(mother's recipe)
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until mixture "spins a thread." Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup slowly into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue to beat while pouring.
Add vanilla and marshmallows.
Beat until thick enough consistency to spread.

title: new potatoes in basil butter
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan of cold water with the sprig of basil.
Bring to boil, then cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Drain and remove basil.
Melt butter in a pan; add chopped basil and cook for 30 seconds, stirring, taking care not to brown the butter.
Toss the potatoes in the butter; spoon into serving dish and garnish with basil sprig.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4. Essential to use fresh basil or half a jar of pesto.

title: beef and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown beef and onion and season with salt and pepper.
Mix soups with milk and combine all other ingredients. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine beef, rice, egg, onion, salt, 1/4 c. tomato soup and worcestershire sauce; mix thoroughly.
Form into meatballs, using about 2 Tbsp. mixture in each one.
Brown meatballs in hot oil. Add remaining tomato soup and water.
Cover and let simmer about 40 minutes or until rice is done.
Yield:
About 2 dozen meatballs.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in white and brown sugars and lemon juice. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch square pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Coat nuts with egg white.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon. Pour over nuts and mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Arrange potatoes in 4 layers in a 2 quart casserole dish; sprinkling each of the first 3 layers with flour, minced onion, salt and pepper. Dot each layer with butter. Sprinkle top layer with onion, salt and pepper. Pour hot milk over top. Bake, covered, 3 minutes. Uncover and bake 1 hour.

title: fruit salad(fresh fruit between layers of fluffy light cream.)
directions: Combine buttermilk and pudding, then fold in whipped topping. Place 1/2 fruit mixture in serving bowl.
Top with pudding, then top with the remaining fruit.

title: peach pickles
directions: Put peaches in large strainer and dip into boiling water for about 1/2 minute. Rinse with cold water and peel. Boil sugar, vinegar and cinnamon 20 minutes. Place 5 or 6 peaches at a time in syrup and boil 5 minutes (or until tender).
Pack in hot jars. Add 1 teaspoon cloves to each jar.
Fil with hot syrup and seal.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain
can
of
salmon and place salmon in large mixing bowl. Add
remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Mixture should
be moist
and
not
too
chunky.
Grease 1 or 2 large skillets lightly
with
oil and heat over medium heat.
Using about
1/4 cup to form each patty 3-inches across and 1/2-inch thick.
Cook, turning
them
once, until golden brown on both sides, about 4 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Toss the chopped broccoli and onion in heated oil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soup; heat to boiling point, then reduce heat.
Stir in cheese, milk and salt; cook 3 minutes longer.
Add cooked rice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
If you use chicken, layer it in the center between top and bottom layers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put a little oil in the bottom of a large iron skillet and heat on stove eye just a minute.
Sprinkle bottom of skillet with a little cornmeal.
Pour mixture into skillet and bake in preheated oven 35 to 40 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: cocoa
directions: Over the lowest possible heat (it doesn't hurt to use a heat diffuser or a double-boiler), combine the cream and water. When they're starting to get warm, add the cocoa, Splenda, protein powder and salt; whisk until well combined. Bring just barely to a simmer and pour into cups. Yield: 2 servings.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice
to
boiling.
Remove at once and pour over jello.
Add
softened	cream cheese.
Mix with mixer and chill until thick (10 to
15 minutes).
Add Dream Whip and 1 cup cut-up pears and chill
until
firm.
Can
be
cut	into squares or molded.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients with mayonnaise. Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smoothly blended. Bake at 350°. Ice as desired after cake is completely cooled.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add water to raisins and boil for 5 minutes, until liquid is decreased to 1/2 cup.
Cool and drain.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, blending well after each.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: let us bake
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, soften and cream Genesis 18.
Slowly beat in Isaiah 7.
In small bowl, beat Job 39 well and add to the creamed mixture.
Sift together the 1 Samuel 28, 1 Kings 19 and Matthew 21, Exodus 30 and Luke 14.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Fold in 2 Samuel 16 and Genesis 43. Grease a 9-inch tube pan with Judges 5.
Line with waxed paper; pour in batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Lower oven temperature to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer, until cake is golden brown and tests done.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.
Remove waxed paper and cool completely.
Yields about 10 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Chop celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar.
Combine ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: pigs feet fiesta
directions: Place pigs
feet,
onion, celery, green pepper, seasonings and vinegar in 8
quart saucepot.
Add 4 cups of water or enough to cover pigs feet.
Bring to a boil.	Reduce to medium heat; cover. Cook 3
hours
or
until pork is tender and meat starts to pull away
from	the
bone.
Stir
in
tomato sauce. Simmer
15 minutes.
Serve
immediately
as
pigs
feet
cool quickly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: smoothie
directions: Combine all the ingredients in blender.
Serve immediately. Makes 1 serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Pour in a Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not preheat oven.
Do not open oven door while baking.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate overnight.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix orange jello and boiling water.
Put this in the refrigerator until firm.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
In an 8-inch square pan, layer the jello, cream cheese mixture, pineapple, 8 ounces Cool Whip and grated cheese, then top with nuts.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Dice onions
and brown with mushrooms in oil.
Beat egg and pour
over	onions and mushrooms.
When egg begins to set, break into pieces.
Add cooked rice, peas, meat and soy sauce. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.	If too dry, add a little water.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute the onions, garlic, bay leaf and peppers in hot oil until onions are translucent.
Add the tomatoes, reserving the juice.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. In a medium skillet, heat oil; add garlic. Stir in reserved liquid from clams and parsley; cook and stir 3 minutes. Add clams, wine, basil and pepper. Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes. Pour sauce over pasta and serve immediately.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 4 to 5 cups water until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to rice.
Bake in shallow dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put in punch bowl in this order:
cake layer, 1/2 of everything in order given, cake layer and 1/2 of everything in order given.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: fruit bars
directions: Make sandwiches with Ritz crackers.
Spread peanut butter between some and Marshmallow Creme between others.
Buy chocolate almond bark and melt it in the microwave.
Dip the cracker sandwiches in the chocolate and you have delicious cookies.
Lay them on foil; they harden instantly.
Keep unused chocolate in refrigerator and melt again later for another batch.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions, peppers and pimentos in large pan. Stir in salt. Soak 1 hour.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes. Add hot peppers to taste. Put in jars and seal. Water bath for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese and Dream Whip together; set aside.
Mix strawberries and filling together.
Mix a layer of cake-strawberry mixture and cream cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Top with sliced strawberries.

title: pennsylvania dutch salad dressing
directions: Whip egg in saucepan.
Add vinegar, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to rolling boil until it thickens.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble bacon.
Add warm salad dressing and crumble bacon to lettuce, endive or other desired greens and toss.

title: mocd legs
directions: You will need round taffy paint stick.

title: german style vegetable soup
directions: Put meat, onions, celery, salt and pepper in large soup pot. Cover with water 1 to 2 inches above contents and cook (covered) over medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender. Add water as necessary.
Add cabbage and can of tomatoes (cut up tomatoes) and continue to cook for about 1 hour or until cabbage is soft.
In separate pots, cook carrots and potatoes until soft (not mushy).
Add cooked carrots, potatoes and tomato soup and simmer until hot.

title: irish stew
directions: In a large heavy skillet, place meat in oil.
Brown; add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Fry until clear.
Add flour and brown (for your roux).
Add bay leaves, thyme and basil.
Add water and Kitchen Bouquet to color.
When meat is getting tender, put in frozen butter beans, carrots and turnips and cook for 15 minutes, then add potatoes, parsley and garlic.
If too thick, add more water and cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with margarine and milk.
Pour over the baked cake. Sprinkle with chocolate bits and chopped nuts.
Dot the remaining cake mix on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 250° and 10 minutes at 350°. This needs no topping.

title: millionaire stuffed shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact; cut a slit almost through back of shrimp, using a paring knife.
Open shrimp and flatten.
Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp; cook 1 minute. Drain.
Place in shallow pan.
Cook onion, green pepper and celery in 1/4 cup butter in a skillet, stirring often, until tender.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together
sugar,
water, corn syrup and salt in a 2 quart casserole.
Loosely
cover
with a lid or plastic wrap. Microwave on
High (100%) for 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling. Uncover. Microwave
on
High
for 8 to 10 minutes, or until
hard ball stage is reached.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and salt.
Pour popped corn into large buttered bowl.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn.
Form into balls.
Great Halloween treats!

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sour cream and egg yolks, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring, flour and soda.
Beat the egg whites in separate bowl until stiff and fold into first mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in 8 wedges.
Arrange wedges peel side down. Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Brush occasionally with oil mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Work butter into flour with pastry blender.
Stir egg and milk together and then into flour.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press the thin edge of apple pieces, in rows, into the dough.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or with a lemon sauce cool.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and layer in bowl with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: julienne beets
directions: Mix and spread over congealed jello.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion in olive oil or vegetable oil in large pot.
Cook hamburg in oil with onion.
Add tomato puree and tomato paste to onions and hamburg.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and oregano; stir and simmer.

title: rachel's oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together in a large bowl the oil, egg, sugar, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: twiggy salad
directions: Cut up a bunch of broccoli into small pieces.
Cut up onions. Add bacon and raisins.
Mix the remainder and pour over.
Chill.

title: apple coconut crisp
directions: Spread apples in 10-inch pie pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, oleo and cinnamon.
Spread over apples.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, egg, coconut, flour and vanilla together; spread over other mixture. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Cook rice (this will make 3 cups of rice) and vegetable medley separately according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish. Place in 350° oven and heat until cheese is melted and is bubbly.

title: kristin's favorite soup
directions: Add cubes to boiling water; simmer for 2 minutes.
Add tomato and garlic powder.
Lower heat; let set for 3 minutes, then add corn, oregano, celery seed and onion.
Bring water to a boil again for 2 minutes; add ham.
Remove from heat.
Add pepper and stir. Serve with toasted bread.

title: "hudsons" maurice salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into the blender. Blend well until all ingredients are mixed. Cover and refrigerate.

title: company or swiss chicken
directions: Place breasts in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Pour soup and water mixture over this.
Mix margarine with stuffing; mix as directed on package directions.
Put on top of chicken.
This can easily be done a day ahead to prepare chicken.
However, wait until ready to bake to put stuffing on top.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, then for 1/2 hour, uncovered. Bake in a 350° oven.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Combine and set aside poppy seed, buttermilk and almond extract.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk and beat.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Fold in beaten stiff egg whites.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ginger ale, and freeze. When preparing to serve, thaw until workable in a punch bowl, then add ginger ale to taste.
(Should be slushy.)
Makes 2 gallons with ginger ale.

title: crab supreme
directions: Cook celery slowly in water 10 minutes and drain.
Spread one-half bread cubes in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread crab, onion, mayonnaise, pepper and celery over bread.
Put the other half of bread on top.
Pour eggs and milk over all. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread soup over top.
Add cheese and paprika.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Great for a luncheon!

title: cheese and broccoli potato topper
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup, sour cream and mustard; add broccoli.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over potatoes.
Garnish with chopped sweet red pepper, if desired. Serves 4.

title: shrimp salad with dressing
directions: Chop up and toss all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Using dressing shown.

title: kansas sunflower seed cookies
directions: *May be purchased at health food store.

title: no bake date cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture bubbles.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Remove from stove. Add pecans, coconut, Rice Krispies, vanilla and salt.
Mixture will be thick.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts, then roll in the powdered sugar.
Makes 40 to 50.
Store in a covered container.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add everything but soup and cook until tender.
Add soup and simmer on low heat until ready to use, 1/2 hour at least.
A small amount of water can be added to prevent sticking.

title: mushroom cheese loaf
directions: Melt butter and seasonings (including onion).
Criss cross cut Vienna bread.
Stuff mushrooms down into cuts then push cheese on top of mushrooms.
Pour butter mixture over top of loaf.
Bake 350 degrees for 40 minutes on a cookie sheet.

title: mike's dip
directions: Heat tomatoes to boiling on stove (may be transferred to crock-pot at this time).
Cube cheese; add gradually.
Reduce heat; continue to stir until melted (if using crock-pot, use high setting).

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Take English muffin, split it and place on baking sheet.
Top with pizza sauce, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted and browned.
Take out and eat!

title: winter strawberries
directions: Combine nuts, coconuts, gelatine, condensed milk and vanilla in medium bowl.
Work until smoothly mixed.
Form into a ball and chill for at least 1 hour.
Shape chilled mixture into strawberries using 1 tablespoon mixture for each strawberry. Chill again, roll strawberries in red sugar, insert stem in each strawberry.
Refrigerate in airtight container until ready to serve.

title: soothing ice sponges(yields 20 servings)
directions: Cut sponges into large approximately 4 x 4-inch and small 2 x 2-inch squares or rectangles.
Moisten sponges with clean water. Place in plastic bag and set in freezer.
Applying ice directly to the skin is harmful and painful.
Sponges cool and soothe the injured area without causing any further pain or injury.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine or shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture. Cover; chill.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon applesauce jello
directions: Place candy in 1 cup of cold water; boil slowly.
Stir so it doesn't stick.
When dissolved, remove from stove; add jello and applesauce.
Pour into mold.

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Measure the corn flakes and crush into crumbs.
Drain off half of the liquid of the salmon.
Combine all ingredients.

title: collector's cocoa cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat 1 minute.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt and add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured round 9-inch pans or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with Seven Minute Frosting.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Grease 13 1/2 x 9 1/2 inch pan.
Spread pineapple in pan with juice.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Place walnuts over mix. Cut margarine into squares and place over walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be served warm or cold. Top with whipped topping.

title: dill biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut biscuits in half.
Dip each piece into butter mixture.
Arrange in single layer in ungreased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.

title: 1880 civil war applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes (do not brown).

title: irish bread
directions: Pour hot water over raisins and drain.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl.
Add shortening and blend well into dry ingredients.
Add sugar and raisins.
Add egg and milk.
Reserve 1 tablespoon milk mixture and brush on top of bread before baking. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Beat egg and milk together; add corn.
Saute onion and chilies in oleo until tender. Add milk mixture, onion mixture and cheese to dry ingredients. Stir until just mixed; pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In large bowl, sift dry ingredients, add nuts, combine strawberries & oil add eggs, Mix well add wet mixture to dry mixture by hand, stir only to blend pour batter into 2 prepared loaf pans bake at 350 for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: minnesota hot dish
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (until carrots are done).

title: sausage and egg brunch casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet; drain.
Place cheese in bottom of greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage over cheese.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Mix soups, mayo, cheese and water. Spray or grease a 9 x 13 pan. Pour less than 1/2 of the soup mixture in the bottom. Next, layer noodles, 1 can of tuna and peas

and repeat with remaining ingredients. Pour remaining soup mixture on top, covering the noodles. Croutons, crushed crackers or dry fine bread crumbs can be put on top, if desired. Cook at 425° for 20 minutes or until bubbling in the middle and enjoy!

title: carnation five minute fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, butter and sugar in pan.
Heat to boil; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups miniature marshmallows, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until melted.
Pour into buttered 8-inch or 9-inch pan. Garnish with nuts.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal in bowl.
Put shortening
in heavy iron skillet and heat.
When corn bread is mixed well and skillet is hot, put in skillet.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This makes a nice crust on the bottom of corn bread.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with lemon juice.
Chop nuts, cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix with cream cheese and add to whipped (stiff) cream.
Use a small amount of the cherry juice to color the mixture.
Freeze.
Serves 8.

title: veggie squares
directions: Roll crescent rolls out onto large cookie sheet, pinching all edges together to form the crust.
Brush egg white on top to ensure even browning.
Bake according to directions on package.
Cool.
Using a mixer, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and envelope of "Dip" mix together until smooth.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Mix carrots, broccoli, and cauliflower together in large mixing bowl.
Spread mixture over cream cheese layer.
Top with cheese.
Cut into squares.

title: grill cheese
directions: Melt butter; place cheese between bread.
Place in pan.
Brown on both sides.
Cool, then serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Bake 48 minutes at 350°.

title: white bean salad vinaigrette
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Very good with crusty French bread.
You may use cilantro, instead of parsley.
Serves 6.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta as package directs.
In large bowl, combine pasta, sausage or ground beef, pasta sauce and 2 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; cover.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. Uncover, top with remaining 2 cups cheese and parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: potato ragout
directions: Cook the potatoes until tender; drain.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet. Add onions and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.

Remove to ovenproof casserole. Add remaining oil to skillet. Add zucchini and cook 5 minutes. Remove to casserole. Add peppers and cook 3 minutes. Remove to casserole. Add tomatoes, oregano, salt, pepper, half each parsley and basil to vegetables in casserole. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Gently fold in potatoes and return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes more, covered. Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes. Add remaining parsley, basil, lemon rind and garlic. Stir.
Serve hot or cold.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Freeze and crush candy bars.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add milk to fill line.
Freeze as usual.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise.
In greased, 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes and pineapple.
Dot each layer with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Pour juice over all. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar with butter, add well beaten eggs. Sift flour with soda; add to cream mixture. Mix 1/2 c. flour with chopped dates, pineapple and nuts. Place by teaspoon on baking sheet, bake 10-15 min at 325° or till golden. May add candied fruit (optional)

title: bottomless crock
directions: In a large bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, oil, mustard, garlic salt and brandy.
Beat until well blended.
Pack into a container, cover and refrigerate for a week before serving.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs one at a time until well blended.
Sift baking powder and salt with flour. Alternate milk and flour.
Beat well, put in tube pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chopped beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; stir in rest of ingredients except sour cream. Simmer, covered, approximately 10 minutes, then add sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: snap, crackle, popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine and caramels over slow heat.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Mix thoroughly.

title: tamale pie
directions: Make a mush by stirring the corn meal and 1 1/2 tablespoons salt into boiling water. Cook 45 minutes. Brown onion in fat. Add the meat and stir until the red color disappears, if meat is raw. Add salt, pepper and tomatoes.
A chopped sweet pepper may be used, if wanted.
Grease baking dish.
Put in layer of corn meal mush.
Add seasoned meat and cover with mush.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for 1 cup pecans.
Chill.
Form into a ball of 2 logs.
Coat with pecans; sprinkle with paprika. Can be frozen.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Take pie crust, sprinkle pecans over the crust.
Bake and cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar, then add Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell.
Pour cooked blueberries over the pie; chill and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust with
cracker
crumbs
and melted margarine. Pat into 13 x 11-inch pan.
Do not bake.

title: date nut bread
directions: Chop dates and nuts. Sprinkle soda over top and then cover with boiling water.
Let stand!
Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and salt. Add dates and nut mixture (undrained). Pour into a loaf pan and bake in a slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: the best hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Fill cup approximately 1/2 full, then fill up with water.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt in regular pot on low heat the peanut butter and butter. Mix sugar, Rice Krispies and butter with the other ingredients together.
Roll in balls.
Put on wax paper.
Put in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate. Dip in ball.
Store in refrigerator 2 hours.
The kind of chocolate you melt in the microwave.
Brand name favorite almond flavoring.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Heat water, milk, butter, salt, white pepper, sour cream and cream cheese to boiling in large saucepan.
Remove from heat. Stir in potato buds just until moistened.
Let stand about 30 seconds or until liquid is absorbed.
Whip with fork until fluffy.
Put potato mixture in 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or put in crock pot, heat for 1 hour and serve from the crock pot.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt the Velveeta in microwave.
Cook the sausage and break in small pieces; drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and serve.

title: sister's hot wassail
directions: Heat and serve hot.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon of hot margarine cook 1/2 chicken until brown.
Remove, set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet, in remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms and onion until vegetables are tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: end-of-world apple cake
directions: Spread pie filling in an 8-inch square cake pan.
Spread cake mix over filling.
Pour butter over top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° until top crusts over.

title: butter coconut pie
directions: Cover pie crust with wax paper and bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle an additional tablespoon of flour over the bottom of the crust.
Pour the rhubarb mixture into the crust.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking another 1/2 hour or until custard is set.

title: eggplant casserole(great!  great!)
directions: Boil eggplant in water to cover until tender, about 30 minutes.
Combine and mix bread and both milks.
Melt oleo and saute onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Add to bread mixture.
Add pimiento, drained eggplant, beaten eggs and all seasonings.
Add 1 cup of cheese; blend all together.
Reserve 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in a greased casserole.
Top with cheese; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a 1-quart glass measuring cup or small mixing bowl.
Beat at high until thick, 2 minutes. Slowly add 1/2 cup oil, a tablespoon at a time.
Beat at high 2 minutes. Beat in vinegar for a minute. Gradually beat in 1 cup oil until thick, 3 to 4 minutes.
Beat in lemon juice.
Makes 2 cups.

title: jam and cheese loaf
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast.
Stir in biscuit mix, egg and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix well.
Turn out onto surface dusted with mix.
Knead gently for 20 strokes.
Place dough on center of baking sheet.
Roll out.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Put pineapple and sugar in a pan and bring to a boil.
Then add Jello and 2 c. cold water.
Then chill for 1/2 hour or until firm.
Then add cheddar cheese and cool whip.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon layer delight
directions: Mix togehter oleo, nuts and flour; pat down in a 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese, add sugar and Cool Whip, then spread over cold crust, set aside.
Make pudding as on box; pour on top of Cool Whip layer.
Spread more Cool Whip on top; then add nuts on top.

title: tostones
directions: Slice green plantains 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Heat 1-inch of oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Fry until light brown on both sides (2 minutes for each side) and drain on paper towels.
Place plantain round between 2 pieces of waxed paper and flatten until 1/8-inch thick.
Add garlic to oil and fry flattened rounds for 3 to 4 minutes per side until golden.
Sprinkle with salt and serve immediately.
A Cuban treat.

title: zucchini squash no-crust pie(may also use pumpkin)
directions: Blend all together. Grease and flour pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped topping.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate square. Mix with other ingredients which have been blended together.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: eggs in a nest
directions: Cut centers from bread with cutter.
Toast cut-out.
Beat egg with milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet.
Place bread in; brown lightly.
Pour egg mixture into cutout part. Cover; cook until egg is set.
Serve with toasted cut-out.

title: mother sawyers' white chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° in 2 (9-inch) pans for about 45 minutes or in large tube pan for about 75 minutes.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Cook potatoes and sausage for 1 hour until almost tender.
Add cabbage.
Season to taste and cook
until desired tenderness.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute meat, breaking into small pieces as it browns.
Add the spaghetti sauce and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients to prepare a cheese filling.
Place a small amount of the sauce in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or casserole dish. Alternate layers of noodles, cheese filling, meat sauce, noodles, filling, noodles and meat sauce.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 deep dish pies or 3 regular size pies.

title: shish kabobs
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine vinegar, mustard, molasses, preserves and ginger.
Alternately thread pork and apples on 6 to 8 skewers.
Brush with sauce.
Grill on an uncovered grill over medium-hot coals, about 12 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, turning and brushing with sauce after 6 minutes.
Or place kabobs on unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 12 to 15 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, turning kabobs and brushing with sauce after 6 minutes.
Heat remaining sauce; pass with kabobs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: walker's rice
directions: In casserole dish, melt butter, then add rice.
Fry until white, then add boiling water.
Add package of soup mix.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover; cook in microwave for 15 minutes on power level 6.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; add salt to taste.
Chill.
Serve with any seafood cocktails.

title: grandma's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar and melted butter.
Whip cream and vanilla; stir into peanut butter mixture. Pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini appetizers(delicious - like spinach pie)
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° in greased 13 x 9-inch pan about 1/2 hour, or until top is light brown; allow to cool.
Cut in squares.
Can be eaten hot or cold.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients and simmer until meat is well done.
If necessary, add enough water to make thick sauce. Put into baking dish and spread cool cornmeal mush over top, touching edges.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Drain fat and put ribs in slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours.

title: moussaka
directions: Brush eggplant slices with oil and sprinkle with salt.
In a large skillet, brown eggplant.
Drain and set aside.
In same skillet, cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is brown; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, wine (if used), parsley, oregano, the 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer for 1 minute. Gradually stir into the beaten egg.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat rice and milk just to boiling.
Cover and simmer until rice is done, about 30 minutes.
Stir every now and then.
Make sure rice is done.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
When rice is done, add egg mixture gradually, stirring all the time.
Let mixture come to a slight boil as it thickens. Pour into dish or cups of your choice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Chill.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and plain flour in a heavy saucepan on medium heat and cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Pour into 2 pie shells, precooked, and place sliced bananas evenly over mixture.
Layer pecans evenly over bananas. Layer sliced cherries over pecans.
Cover with coconut (optional). Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate both pies 2 hours before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: peanut-cherry fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine peanut butter chips and sweetened milk in the top of a double boiler.
Place over hot water.
Heat slowly, stirring often, until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from hot water.
Stir in vanilla and cherries.
Spoon into pan, spreading evenly.
Mark top into 36 pieces.
Trim each piece with a sliver of candied cherry.
Chill until firm.
Finish cutting into squares.
Stor in tightly covered container.
Yields 3 dozen squares.

title: blueberry shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium-high until mixture becomes creamy.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chinese salad
directions: Cool Rice-A-Roni in refrigerator.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir together.
Best if sets for 12 to 24 hours.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease loaf pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cocoa chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, 1/2 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into a small bowl.
Add egg yolks, oil, water and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Beat at medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes. Wash beaters.
Beat egg whites until they are foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into egg mixture; fold until blended.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then increase temperature to 350° and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: ole settlers baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef, bacon and onion.
Add and mix the rest of the ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shell(s).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: No mixing, make right in baking pan.

title: bulgarian beef stew
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add onions, garlic and bay leaves, saut onions until golden brown.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper, add to pot.
Add paprika, lemon peel, savory and cayenne pepper, stir until meat gets coated.
Add beef broth and wine, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover, simmer meat for 90 minutes, stirring occasionally until it is tender.
Using a slotted spoon transfer meat to a bowl.
In a small bowl mix butter and flour until a smooth paste forms.
Add to liquid in pot.
Simmer until liquid thickens, about 8-10 minutes.
Return meat to pot and set on low heat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Serve stew over egg noodles.
Sprinkle with dashes of fresh parsley.
Serves 6.

title: raisin nut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Sift flour with salt.
Beat eggs with sugar, then beat in oil and rum extract.
Stir in flour mixture, alternately with raisin mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on cake rack.
Serve warm, topped with ice cream.
Makes 20 servings.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/8 teaspoon each pepper, sage and thyme.
Shape firmly into 6 mini meat loaves.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: After measuring the Rice Krispies; crush and blend with margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Mix with hands.
Form mixture into balls.
Melt chocolate over hot water and dip the balls into the chocolate.
Put dipped balls on waxed paper.

title: kourambiethes (powdered sugar cookies)(international:  nigeria)
directions: In bowl mix butter, powdered sugar and egg yolk.
Beat well. In a separate bowl sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Gradually add dry mixture to cream mixture.
Turn mixture out on a floured board and knead until smooth.
Pinch off small amounts at a time and form into flattened balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet, about 3/4-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and roll immediately in powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon nut loaf
directions: Combine sugars, cinnamon and walnuts.
Dip biscuits in butter, then in sugar mixture. Stand biscuits on edge in greased 9-inch ring mold.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. If desired, loaf can be iced with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Place in a small baking dish. Spread evenly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until tender.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Add bacon.
Chop broccoli and add some onion and raisins.
Pour liquid over and serve!

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, cocoa, butter, milk, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Mix well, then pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (stir well after each thing you add).

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add to batter.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in vanilla, apple and pecans.
Bake in greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add soup, milk, pepper and taters.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce to low.
Cover and let simmer for 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: seven layer salad *
directions: Arrange in bowl by layers, seal and chill overnight.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: lo-cal colada(serves 6)
directions: Blend all ingredients in an electric blender until smooth.
A great alternative to soda.

title: spaghetti con vongole ed acciughe(spaghetti with clams and anchovies)
directions: Saute onions in oil until soft.
Add clam liquid and anchovies.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in peppers and garlic. Cook for 15 minutes.
Add clams and cook for 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti al dente, drain and place in warm bowl.
Pour clam sauce over spaghetti and toss.
Serve in hot bowls.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hearty nacho dip
directions: Prepare taco mix with hamburger as directed on package.
Add chili beans and chilies.
Heat through.
Melt Cheddar on top. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on low heat or in a double boiler.
Dilute with milk.
Serve with French bread; cut into cubes.
Keep hot.

title: amish sugar cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients together; cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Let cool, then refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into 3 well-greased No. 303 (1-pound) tin cans.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Remove from cans; let cool on rack.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: stir-fry oriental chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken breasts into very thin strips; brown in hot oil. As chicken begins to turn white, add chopped onion.
When onion is clear, add celery and stir-fry quickly.
Add broth, soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Add water chestnuts and cook only until they are heated through.
Add cornstarch and water mixture and continue cooking until gravy thickens.
Serve over cooked rice.
May be topped with slivered toasted almonds.

title: quick 'n golden quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes; reduce oven to 375°.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, syrup, nuts, and dates and beaten egg in a large skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly until soft ball forms in cold water.
Add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Roll into 2 long rolls.
Then roll them in powdered sugar or coconut. Refrigerate until firm.
Slice.

title: orange coffee
directions: Place all ingredients, except orange slices, in a blender and blend at medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour into frosted glasses and garnish each with an orange slice.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Melt chocolate; add egg yolks, milk and regular sugar to chocolate.
Stir until smooth.
When mixture starts to thicken, take off heat and allow to cool.

title: barbecued chicken skillet style
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Wash, salt and pepper chicken and place in pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover; cook on low for 1 hour.
Turn over after 30 minutes.

title: orange cream souffle
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add gelatin mixture, cold water and orange juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into buttered souffle dish or individual molds.
May be used as salad or as dessert.

title: pork chops with spaghetti
directions: Brown the chops well in hot shortening.
Remove pork chops and cook the onion until tender.
Add spaghetti and seasoning. Pour tomato soup with equal amount of water over spaghetti.
Place chops over the top.
Cover closely and let simmer about 1 hour. Before serving, sprinkle cheese over the top.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 2-quart casserole, microwave on High 4 minutes.
Take out; stir and return to microwave.
Microwave 4 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir quickly and pour in well buttered cookie sheet.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook
and
clean
shrimp.
Saute
onion
and margarine. Make a sauce mixing soup, lemon juice and seasonings.
Fold in shrimp and rice.
Fold
in
sour cream.
Pour into quart buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and garnish with peppers after parboiling 2 minutes.

title: apple butter crescents
directions: Unroll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Spread 1 teaspoon over each of the 8 triangles.
Roll each and place on cookie sheet.
Bake crescents as directed on package label.

title: chicken diane
directions: Cook chicken in butter in heavy skillet, 10 minutes on each side.
Reserve pan drippings.
Put chicken on platter, keep warm. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire, mustard and salt to pan drippings.
Cook, stirring until heated.
Stir in onions and parsley.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Add eggs. Stir in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
I bake 50 minutes in a glass pie plate.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Add bananas and add nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes two loaves.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased muffin pan at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Add Wesson oil and sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat.
Add apricot nectar.
Beat.
Add cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add drained vegetables and thicken with 1/2 cup cornstarch, mixed with the 1/2 cup of vinegar.
Simmer for a few minutes; put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Mix in flour, salt and baking soda.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Shape into small balls.
Press tops with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon crisp.
Remove drippings, return to pot.
Add onion and cook until lightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 5 minutes.
Crumble bacon over chowder and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cornbread dressing mix on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Cook noodles and spinach according to package.
Drain noodles and place in large bowl.
Add spinach, drained, eggs and cheese. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat with onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add sauce and paste.
Add water if needed for right consistency.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Spread sauce over noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and let set about 5 minutes before cutting into portions.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Scald the 1 quart of milk in a double boiler.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, beaten eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Add to the scalded milk and cook.
Stir until thickened (about 4 minutes). Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and serve garnished with fruit.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in egg mixture.

title: finnish meatloaf in sour cream pastry(also known as lihamurekepiiras)
directions: Sift flour and salt together in chilled bowl. Cut chilled butter in 1/4-inch pieces and cut into flour.

title: fondue
directions: Cut the bread into small cubes, making sure that most pieces have some crust.
Grate the cheeses.
Mix wine with cornstarch and stir into cheeses. Bring mixture over low heat to a boil.
Add garlic, Kirsch, pepper, paprika and nutmeg.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Combine all ingredients except crackers. Grease large baking pan. Put mixture into baking pan, pat down. Then crumble your crackers over the top and dot with margarine. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until top gets brown and bubbly.

title: swedish rice meat balls
directions: Combine rie, beef, egg, onion, salt, nutmeg, pepper and milk. Mixing lightly, shape into balls.
Place in skillet.
Blend soup with water and lemon juice.
Pour over meat balls and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 24 meat balls or 2 servings.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cracker pie
directions: Let come to a boil the sugar, water and 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Break crackers into pieces in pie crust.
Chip butter over top.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Pour sugar water mixture on crackers. Cut pie crust into strips and lay over top, then sprinkle with more cinnamon.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine tomato sauce, garbanzo beans, faijoles beans, onion, tomatoes and taco seasoning, in a
5 quart dutch oven.
Simmer over low heat until onions are done and flavors mix.
Serve hot topped with sour cream or shredded cheese.
Nachos as a side.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish. Mix bread crumbs and butter together. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fudge kisses(fun and easy to make with your preschooler!)
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk together for 1 minute, slowly stirring.
Remove from heat, add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender; set aside. Prepare rice mix as package directs.
Add chicken, cheese, milk and onion-pepper mixture to prepared rice; mix well.
Heat 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onion.
Drain fat.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add hamburger mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven until done.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda together. Beat eggs, sugar, oil and strawberries (thawed) together. Add the flour mixture and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Cook the ground beef and sausage in a large saucepan until color changes. Add onion, garlic, water, tomato paste, pepper and salt. Bring to a boil; simmer 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cream together milk and cream cheese. Add lemon juice.
Fill pie shell with mixture.
Chill 2 hours. Top with favorite pie filling.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in mold or muffin rings. Freeze.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Peel and cut bad places from apples.
Cut apples into quarters.
Add water.
Cook apples very slowly, stirring often. Apples will stick and burn if not stirred often.
If apples look too thick, add more water a little at a time.
When done, remove a few at a time and run through a colander.
Freeze or can applesauce.
Add sugar and spices at time of use.

title: banana pudding(no cooking required)
directions: Combine milk and water.
Add pudding and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1 cup mixture into 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Top with 1/3 each wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat twice.
End with pudding.
Cover and chill.

title: country cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage on fine cutter.
Put in frypan with butter and salt.
Cook on low.
Toss lightly with fork until salt begins to draw water from cabbage.
Cover; stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Cook until cabbage is tender, about 20 minutes.
Be careful not to let cabbage brown.
(The secret of success is to steam the cabbage until tender, but keep it white.)
Beat egg; add cream and vinegar.
Stir lightly; pour over cabbage.
Let come to a boil and serve at once with paprika sprinkled on top.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix all together and beat until well blended and fluffy.

title: boneless chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch flat pan.
Put Swiss cheese over chicken breasts.
Combine soup, white wine, stuffing and melted butter together; pour on top of chicken and cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well. Add milk, sweet potatoes, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican dish
directions: Mix soup and tomatoes together; set aside.
Brown hamburger meat and drain off fat.
Grate cheese.
Crush tortilla chips in bag.
Layer chips, hamburger, beans, soup and tomatoes.
Mix together and grate cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine the Italian dressing, vinegar and curry powder.
Add to rice mixture; toss well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 4 servings (about 95 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: sausage balls
directions: Work uncooked sausage into Bisquick and grated cheese.
Roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 100 balls.
You can freeze them, too.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots with 1 teaspoon of salt to your liking.
They are good crispy.
Cool before mixing all together.
Enjoy!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Crumble half in bottom of bowl. Layer with pineapple, pie filling and pudding, using half of each ingredient.
Repeat and then add Cool Whip.
Use nuts on top, if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl in layers.
Cover in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours.
Will keep in refrigerator for one week.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together until creamy.
Add spices.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Saute bell pepper in oil in skillet until tender.
Roll out dough on floured surface into a 12 x 24-inch rectangle.
Arrange Provolone cheese, pepperoni and bell peppers down center of dough, overlapping slices.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and garlic salt over top.
Fold sides to enclose filling.
Seal seam and ends well. Brush top of loaf with oil.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice into serving portions.

title: mrs. audice's potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix flour, cocoa and spices together.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Add mashed potatoes and nuts.
May be baked in layers or a Bundt pan.
Seven minute icing is suggested.
For a layer cake, bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes; for Bundt cake, bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
When toothpick comes out clean, cake is done.

title: hot chocolate drink
directions: Mix all ingredients together in gallon jar.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons in a cup of hot water.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk, beating until thick.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer mixture alternately with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Makes a very large bowl full.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add pineapple (including juice) and rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour into rectangular dish and top with the following topping.

title: hot cheese potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
When done, add Cheez Whiz.
Set aside. Saute together the onion, celery and green pepper in the margarine.
Set aside.
In another pan, cook chopped broccoli until tender. Drain. Put all ingredients together and add the cream of mushroom soup. Bake in flat dish 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well and serve.
Can be frozen.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Put uncooked macaroni in 6 cups boiling water.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes and drain.
Brown ground beef and add next 4 ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Layer in greased dish (or dishes) macaroni, cottage cheese and tomato-ground beef mixture.
Alternate again.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
